WEBVTT

1
00:00:39.539 --> 00:00:41.082
[man] There's still
so many things

2
00:00:41.166 --> 00:00:42.709
we don't understand
about this case.

3
00:00:42.792 --> 00:00:44.044
and probably never will.

4
00:00:46.629 --> 00:00:48.256
We just had bits and pieces

5
00:00:48.339 --> 00:00:51.551
of some kind
of strange puzzle.

6
00:00:51.634 --> 00:00:55.138
And even if we could put them
all together.

7
00:00:55.221 --> 00:00:57.265
I don't know if I want to see
whatever picture they make.

8
00:00:59.350 --> 00:01:06.191
[tense music playing]

9
00:01:17.660 --> 00:01:19.496
[clears throat]

10
00:01:19.579 --> 00:01:20.705
-[producer whispers]
-Yeah.

11
00:01:20.789 --> 00:01:22.540
Uh-huh.

12
00:01:22.624 --> 00:01:24.042
My name is Joseph Kirby.

13
00:01:24.125 --> 00:01:26.169
I'm a former
lead detective sergeant

14
00:01:26.252 --> 00:01:28.046
in San Bernardino County.

15
00:01:28.129 --> 00:01:30.507
I was supervising
the Major Crimes Unit

16
00:01:30.590 --> 00:01:33.510
between 2007 and 2015.

17
00:01:34.844 --> 00:01:37.138
San Bernardino County
is about 60 miles east

18
00:01:37.222 --> 00:01:38.473
of Los Angeles.

19
00:01:38.556 --> 00:01:39.849
It is a part of California's

20
00:01:39.933 --> 00:01:42.393
Inland Empire region.

21
00:01:42.477 --> 00:01:44.771
We have a population
of about two million.

22
00:01:44.854 --> 00:01:46.648
We've seen
our share of violent crimes.

23
00:01:46.731 --> 00:01:48.149
gang-related homicides.

24
00:01:48.233 --> 00:01:49.943
relatively large-scale
drug busts.

25
00:01:50.026 --> 00:01:50.985
what have you.

26
00:01:51.069 --> 00:01:52.195
We probably run

27
00:01:52.278 --> 00:01:56.825
upwards of 65 murders a year

28
00:01:56.908 --> 00:01:59.744
in the San Bernardino County
Sheriff's Homicide Bureau.

29
00:01:59.828 --> 00:02:02.455
which is higher
than the national average.

30
00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:04.624
But I had never seen
anything like what happened

31
00:02:04.707 --> 00:02:07.127
to the Sheridan family
on Alton Avenue.

32
00:02:08.044 --> 00:02:09.129
Nobody had.

33
00:02:09.212 --> 00:02:11.464
[dial tone]

34
00:02:11.548 --> 00:02:13.675
[dispatcher] 911.
what is your emergency?

35
00:02:13.758 --> 00:02:14.467
[female voice]

36
00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:24.102
[dispatcher]

37
00:02:24.185 --> 00:02:25.937
[female voice] My name...

38
00:02:26.020 --> 00:02:28.022
My name is Kacie Porter.

39
00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:32.485
and I was friends
with Tiffany Sheridan.

40
00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:35.613
Our kids went
to the same elementary school.

41
00:02:35.697 --> 00:02:38.074
[laughs]
When you have kids that age.

42
00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:41.786
and you meet a lot of parents
that you don't always care for.

43
00:02:41.870 --> 00:02:46.207
but Tiff and I.
we just hit it off.

44
00:02:46.291 --> 00:02:49.085
We were supposed to meet
at this restaurant for lunch.

45
00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:51.713
but she never showed.
and I just...

46
00:02:51.796 --> 00:02:56.301
I figured she had forgotten.
so I let it go.

47
00:02:56.384 --> 00:02:58.803
But then Lauren came home.
and she said

48
00:02:58.887 --> 00:03:01.848
that Sam hadn't been
to school in a few days.

49
00:03:01.931 --> 00:03:03.683
And. um. I kept calling

50
00:03:03.766 --> 00:03:07.604
and I kept texting.
but I never got a reply back.

51
00:03:09.105 --> 00:03:12.150
And I just knew.
in the back of my head.

52
00:03:12.233 --> 00:03:14.360
that something is wrong.

53
00:03:23.369 --> 00:03:26.080
[operator]

54
00:03:26.164 --> 00:03:27.707
I'm Will Martinez.

55
00:03:27.790 --> 00:03:29.167
I'm a deputy sheriff

56
00:03:29.250 --> 00:03:31.419
with the San Bernardino
Sheriff's Department.

57
00:03:31.502 --> 00:03:32.879
Me and my partner
were the first officers

58
00:03:32.962 --> 00:03:35.048
to arrive on scene.

59
00:03:35.131 --> 00:03:37.050
We got a call
regarding a welfare check

60
00:03:37.133 --> 00:03:39.510
for a residence
in the Shandin Hills.

61
00:03:39.594 --> 00:03:41.512
Nice area.

62
00:03:41.596 --> 00:03:44.849
It was a gated community.
as I remember.

63
00:03:44.933 --> 00:03:51.773
[tense music playing]

64
00:03:58.154 --> 00:03:59.239
The whole thing felt weird.

65
00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:02.659
Something about it
was just off.

66
00:04:02.742 --> 00:04:04.744
[tense music playing]

67
00:04:04.827 --> 00:04:05.954
Police department!

68
00:04:09.666 --> 00:04:10.792
Police department!

69
00:04:10.875 --> 00:04:12.043
Anybody home?

70
00:04:12.126 --> 00:04:15.004
[woman speaking on radio]

71
00:04:15.088 --> 00:04:19.342
[tense music playing]

72
00:04:19.425 --> 00:04:20.510
[Martinez]
We need to go around.

73
00:04:29.894 --> 00:04:32.021
Police department! Anyone home?

74
00:04:41.072 --> 00:04:42.991
My partner called out.

75
00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:45.076
identified ourselves again.

76
00:04:45.159 --> 00:04:46.119
but there was no movement.

77
00:04:47.745 --> 00:04:48.746
Hello?

78
00:04:52.625 --> 00:04:53.626
Anybody home?

79
00:04:53.710 --> 00:04:57.672
[tense music playing]

80
00:04:59.007 --> 00:05:00.758
[whispering]
Mother of God.

81
00:05:00.842 --> 00:05:03.052
[tense music playing]

82
00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:04.804
This was a crime scene.

83
00:05:04.887 --> 00:05:11.728
[tense music playing]

84
00:05:15.857 --> 00:05:17.483
[Kacie] Oh.
what happened to them...

85
00:05:19.319 --> 00:05:22.238
I think about it every day.

86
00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:24.407
I have nightmares about it.

87
00:05:24.490 --> 00:05:30.330
[tense music playing]

88
00:05:32.248 --> 00:05:34.042
Why them?

89
00:05:34.125 --> 00:05:40.173
[tense music playing]

90
00:05:40.256 --> 00:05:43.134
That... was a bad day.

91
00:05:43.217 --> 00:05:50.308
[tense music playing]

92
00:05:57.857 --> 00:06:01.694
When I saw that. I was...

93
00:06:01.778 --> 00:06:03.905
floored.

94
00:06:03.988 --> 00:06:05.323
I looked at my partner
and I said.

95
00:06:05.406 --> 00:06:08.951
"Oh. my God. he's back."

96
00:06:09.035 --> 00:06:14.248
[dramatic music playing]

97
00:06:53.955 --> 00:06:55.373
Hi.

98
00:06:55.456 --> 00:06:56.916
My name's Lexi Taylor.

99
00:06:56.999 --> 00:06:58.835
I'm a senior homicide detective

100
00:06:58.918 --> 00:07:01.170
for the San Bernardino P.D.

101
00:07:01.254 --> 00:07:03.881
I worked as a patrol officer
for about nine years

102
00:07:03.965 --> 00:07:06.259
before being offered
a job in the homicide bureau.

103
00:07:06.342 --> 00:07:08.302
and that's when I started
working with my partner.

104
00:07:08.386 --> 00:07:10.138
Joe Kirby.

105
00:07:10.221 --> 00:07:12.515
Growing up.
my mom worked two jobs

106
00:07:12.598 --> 00:07:14.517
to support me
and my older brother.

107
00:07:14.600 --> 00:07:17.562
There was a rotating door
of less-than-great men.

108
00:07:17.645 --> 00:07:19.939
you would say.
come and go in our life.

109
00:07:20.022 --> 00:07:21.524
I think that's
when I first started

110
00:07:21.607 --> 00:07:23.067
thinking that.
maybe. I would like

111
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:24.861
to try to help people.

112
00:07:24.944 --> 00:07:26.362
You know.
maybe I could help someone

113
00:07:26.446 --> 00:07:29.740
like my mom
out of a tough situation.

114
00:07:29.824 --> 00:07:31.951
I actually never intended
to be a cop.

115
00:07:32.034 --> 00:07:35.746
I had aspirations of being
a drummer in a metal band.

116
00:07:35.830 --> 00:07:37.915
But one of my friend's brothers

117
00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:40.835
was in the Academy.
and I thought it sounded cool.

118
00:07:40.918 --> 00:07:42.712
I liked how you had
to think on your feet.

119
00:07:42.795 --> 00:07:44.881
use your brain
as well as your body.

120
00:07:44.964 --> 00:07:47.258
After a couple of days
in training.

121
00:07:47.341 --> 00:07:49.510
I was hooked. man.

122
00:07:51.179 --> 00:07:52.430
[Taylor] That is
how I have always approached

123
00:07:52.513 --> 00:07:54.682
my career in law enforcement.

124
00:07:54.765 --> 00:07:57.268
Try to be there for people
when things are at their worst.

125
00:07:58.978 --> 00:08:01.481
And. fuck. it was never worse
than on this case.

126
00:08:03.191 --> 00:08:06.694
Between 1993 and 1995.
there were three murders

127
00:08:06.777 --> 00:08:09.322
in Riverside
and San Bernardino County

128
00:08:09.405 --> 00:08:12.742
that we eventually
realized were serial murders.

129
00:08:12.825 --> 00:08:17.246
and which had
some ritualistic aspects.

130
00:08:24.045 --> 00:08:26.047
[man] I think this is it.

131
00:08:26.130 --> 00:08:28.341
Yeah.

132
00:08:28.424 --> 00:08:30.843
Okay. she was covered
with a blue tarp.

133
00:08:30.927 --> 00:08:33.429
You could see it
easily from the road.

134
00:08:33.513 --> 00:08:35.640
This is a service road.
not a lot of people

135
00:08:35.723 --> 00:08:37.558
come down it.

136
00:08:37.642 --> 00:08:39.477
It was just horrible.
I mean. you never expect

137
00:08:39.560 --> 00:08:41.270
to see something like that.

138
00:08:43.272 --> 00:08:45.399
[Kirby] On August 8th. 1993.

139
00:08:45.483 --> 00:08:48.819
the torso of 24-year-old
Shifra Gutierrez

140
00:08:48.903 --> 00:08:50.196
is discovered
in San Bernardino

141
00:08:50.279 --> 00:08:51.531
National Forest.

142
00:08:52.865 --> 00:08:54.367
She had been dismembered.

143
00:08:55.576 --> 00:08:57.995
Her genitals mutilated.

144
00:08:58.079 --> 00:09:00.623
The uterus removed.

145
00:09:00.706 --> 00:09:02.208
The coroner gave
a best-guess estimate

146
00:09:02.291 --> 00:09:03.584
she had been there two weeks.

147
00:09:03.668 --> 00:09:05.711
but it's difficult to tell.

148
00:09:08.506 --> 00:09:09.507
[woman]
Shifra was my best friend

149
00:09:09.590 --> 00:09:10.550
in high school.

150
00:09:12.343 --> 00:09:13.469
She was a dope bitch.

151
00:09:13.553 --> 00:09:14.762
[laughs]

152
00:09:16.180 --> 00:09:17.765
She just had
this joy for living.

153
00:09:17.848 --> 00:09:20.601
and this lust for life.
you know?

154
00:09:20.685 --> 00:09:22.395
And she was funny as fuck.

155
00:09:24.939 --> 00:09:26.983
She wasn't a bad person.

156
00:09:27.066 --> 00:09:29.527
You know. she just...

157
00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:31.195
I don't know. she just
got into some bad shit.

158
00:09:31.279 --> 00:09:33.489
like a lot of people
out here do.

159
00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:35.825
I was always telling her.
I was like.

160
00:09:35.908 --> 00:09:37.326
"This is dangerous. Shifra.

161
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:38.869
You know.
you gotta stop doing this."

162
00:09:40.246 --> 00:09:42.373
Oh. shit. I said
I wasn't going to do this.

163
00:09:43.874 --> 00:09:46.836
[Taylor]
There's an area off the 91

164
00:09:46.919 --> 00:09:48.337
in the Casablanca
neighborhood.

165
00:09:48.421 --> 00:09:50.965
and that's where Shifra
was last seen.

166
00:09:51.048 --> 00:09:53.551
We do know she went up
to a room at a motel

167
00:09:53.634 --> 00:09:56.679
called Dean's Corner that was
frequented by sex workers.

168
00:09:56.762 --> 00:09:58.889
And there was
a man with her. but...

169
00:09:58.973 --> 00:10:01.225
clerk couldn't remember
what he looked like.

170
00:10:01.309 --> 00:10:02.852
He could've killed her there.

171
00:10:02.935 --> 00:10:04.854
Could've been strangulation.
for example.

172
00:10:04.937 --> 00:10:06.439
We'll probably never know.

173
00:10:06.522 --> 00:10:07.565
What we do know for sure

174
00:10:07.648 --> 00:10:09.317
is that she was somehow moved

175
00:10:09.400 --> 00:10:12.028
from that room
without anybody noticing.

176
00:10:12.111 --> 00:10:14.614
Or somebody noticed
and just didn't care.

177
00:10:15.948 --> 00:10:17.325
But we got our first lead.

178
00:10:18.367 --> 00:10:20.328
A name.

179
00:10:20.411 --> 00:10:22.121
All guests
had to fill out a ledger.

180
00:10:22.204 --> 00:10:23.414
and the suspect
had written down

181
00:10:23.497 --> 00:10:25.916
the name Albert Shiny.

182
00:10:27.376 --> 00:10:29.295
And the case went cold.

183
00:10:29.378 --> 00:10:31.672
I don't need to tell you that.
especially at that time.

184
00:10:31.756 --> 00:10:33.883
sex workers
and marginalized people

185
00:10:33.966 --> 00:10:35.468
tended to get
the short end of the stick

186
00:10:35.551 --> 00:10:37.470
in the criminal justice system.

187
00:10:37.553 --> 00:10:38.304
I'm not saying it was right.

188
00:10:38.387 --> 00:10:39.847
I'm just saying it was.

189
00:10:39.930 --> 00:10:41.682
and is the reality.

190
00:10:43.517 --> 00:10:45.811
So. it was written off
as an isolated incident.

191
00:10:47.605 --> 00:10:50.900
But we were wrong.

192
00:10:50.983 --> 00:10:53.319
A grisly crime scene
has police on high alert

193
00:10:53.402 --> 00:10:54.987
in Arlanza tonight.

194
00:10:55.071 --> 00:10:57.281
not far from the Riverside
Municipal Airport.

195
00:10:57.365 --> 00:10:59.659
where the body of 82-year-old
Ambrose Griffith

196
00:10:59.742 --> 00:11:00.951
was discovered murdered

197
00:11:01.035 --> 00:11:02.495
in his apartment
earlier today.

198
00:11:02.578 --> 00:11:04.497
Mr. Griffith was disabled
and. apparently.

199
00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:06.749
suffered from MDS.
a blood condition

200
00:11:06.832 --> 00:11:09.168
that required daily assistance
from a caretaker.

201
00:11:09.251 --> 00:11:11.587
[Kirby] Nine months after
Shifra Gutierrez is killed.

202
00:11:11.671 --> 00:11:13.005
Ambrose Griffith
is found murdered

203
00:11:13.089 --> 00:11:15.091
in his assisted
living facility.

204
00:11:15.174 --> 00:11:18.511
On the night of June 3rd. 1994.

205
00:11:18.594 --> 00:11:20.429
someone scaled the back side
of his building

206
00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:22.598
and entered his unit
through a sliding glass door

207
00:11:22.682 --> 00:11:24.433
that was apparently
left unlocked.

208
00:11:26.143 --> 00:11:27.895
He was bludgeoned
with an oxygen tank

209
00:11:27.978 --> 00:11:29.438
that was in his room.

210
00:11:29.522 --> 00:11:31.148
and then stabbed
more than 30 times

211
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:32.858
with a box cutter.

212
00:11:32.942 --> 00:11:34.360
That was brutal.

213
00:11:34.443 --> 00:11:35.986
And you gotta understand.
this guy was bedbound.

214
00:11:36.070 --> 00:11:37.279
I mean. he could not walk.

215
00:11:37.363 --> 00:11:39.198
or could barely walk.
on his own.

216
00:11:39.281 --> 00:11:41.951
So. he was totally defenseless
to the attack.

217
00:11:42.034 --> 00:11:44.161
which was
obviously unprovoked.

218
00:11:44.245 --> 00:11:46.288
No one else in the building
heard so much as a peep

219
00:11:46.372 --> 00:11:47.998
from his room.

220
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:52.002
So. it must've happened fast.
which is...

221
00:11:53.295 --> 00:11:54.672
some comfort. I guess.

222
00:11:56.215 --> 00:11:57.758
One of his eyes
was also removed.

223
00:11:57.842 --> 00:11:59.468
[Taylor]
It was a sloppy scene.

224
00:11:59.552 --> 00:12:01.512
A murder committed
by somebody in a frenzy

225
00:12:01.595 --> 00:12:03.597
who was not thinking it
through at all.

226
00:12:03.681 --> 00:12:05.808
It's probably why we were able
to get our first real clue.

227
00:12:07.935 --> 00:12:09.228
[Kirby] The print was run
through the system.

228
00:12:09.311 --> 00:12:10.771
but nothing came back.

229
00:12:10.855 --> 00:12:12.523
The lab guys
stayed on it for weeks.

230
00:12:12.606 --> 00:12:14.233
but it was only a partial.

231
00:12:14.316 --> 00:12:15.568
No motive.

232
00:12:15.651 --> 00:12:16.902
82-year-old victim

233
00:12:16.986 --> 00:12:18.821
with no family and few friends.

234
00:12:18.904 --> 00:12:20.948
except the few people
that lived in his building

235
00:12:21.031 --> 00:12:23.367
who were just
as sick as he was.

236
00:12:23.451 --> 00:12:24.827
So. the police didn't make
any connection

237
00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:26.620
with the Gutierrez murder.

238
00:12:26.704 --> 00:12:28.038
Not yet.

239
00:12:28.122 --> 00:12:30.166
[sobs]

240
00:12:30.249 --> 00:12:31.292
[man] It's okay. It's okay.

241
00:12:31.375 --> 00:12:33.544
It's okay. It's okay.

242
00:12:33.627 --> 00:12:34.879
We want to thank everyone

243
00:12:34.962 --> 00:12:37.006
from the Riverside
Police Department

244
00:12:37.089 --> 00:12:38.382
with their continued support.

245
00:12:40.092 --> 00:12:41.677
Someone out there

246
00:12:41.761 --> 00:12:43.387
knows what happened
to our little boy. and...

247
00:12:43.471 --> 00:12:44.638
and...

248
00:12:47.933 --> 00:12:49.393
[voice breaking]
We are begging

249
00:12:49.477 --> 00:12:50.436
for you to help us

250
00:12:50.519 --> 00:12:53.022
return him home

251
00:12:53.105 --> 00:12:55.399
safely and unharmed.

252
00:12:55.483 --> 00:12:56.776
[Kirby] Noah Lafone
was abducted

253
00:12:56.859 --> 00:12:58.152
while walking home from school

254
00:12:58.235 --> 00:13:01.113
on October 7th. 1995.

255
00:13:01.197 --> 00:13:02.573
He was 12 years old.

256
00:13:03.699 --> 00:13:05.034
There were no witnesses.

257
00:13:05.117 --> 00:13:08.287
and pretty much
no information to go on.

258
00:13:08.370 --> 00:13:10.956
There was
a pretty extensive search

259
00:13:11.040 --> 00:13:13.876
and media effort this time
to try to find him.

260
00:13:13.959 --> 00:13:15.836
We were doing door-to-doors.

261
00:13:15.920 --> 00:13:18.714
This was the first case
I was on involving a child.

262
00:13:18.798 --> 00:13:21.091
so I really threw myself
into it.

263
00:13:21.675 --> 00:13:25.054
I'd get off work and I'd go
join Search and Rescue.

264
00:13:25.137 --> 00:13:26.806
People put
in hundreds of hours.

265
00:13:26.889 --> 00:13:29.141
but days turned into weeks

266
00:13:29.225 --> 00:13:32.937
and it gets harder and harder
to stay positive.

267
00:13:33.020 --> 00:13:35.022
Three months later. in January.

268
00:13:35.105 --> 00:13:36.899
his body is discovered
in a shallow creek

269
00:13:36.982 --> 00:13:38.400
near Silverwood Lake.

270
00:13:42.738 --> 00:13:45.157
He had been weighed down
by concrete bricks.

271
00:13:45.241 --> 00:13:47.535
and his body
was in pretty bad shape.

272
00:13:47.618 --> 00:13:50.037
[tense music playing]

273
00:13:50.120 --> 00:13:51.497
There were
multiple lacerations

274
00:13:51.580 --> 00:13:53.123
to his abdomen.

275
00:13:53.207 --> 00:13:54.667
and his liver
had been removed.

276
00:13:55.835 --> 00:13:56.877
Twelve years old.

277
00:13:58.587 --> 00:13:59.505
Whole life ahead of him.

278
00:14:00.923 --> 00:14:01.966
Poof.

279
00:14:03.217 --> 00:14:05.886
We also found a box cutter.
the weapon.

280
00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:07.555
as well as Noah's
school backpack

281
00:14:07.638 --> 00:14:09.723
and all its contents.

282
00:14:09.807 --> 00:14:12.309
This is where we got
our second lead.

283
00:14:12.393 --> 00:14:13.936
It was a page
that had been written on

284
00:14:14.019 --> 00:14:15.563
and then torn out.

285
00:14:15.646 --> 00:14:17.731
but you could still see
an imprint.

286
00:14:19.608 --> 00:14:20.693
Kaliban.

287
00:14:21.735 --> 00:14:24.113
What the heck was kaliban?

288
00:14:24.196 --> 00:14:26.073
A bird from the Caribbean.
we found out.

289
00:14:26.156 --> 00:14:28.325
Or a character
from Shakespeare.

290
00:14:28.409 --> 00:14:29.994
I mean. was this
some kind of a code?

291
00:14:30.077 --> 00:14:32.746
Was this
another Zodiac Killer?

292
00:14:32.830 --> 00:14:34.707
Then. two weeks after
his body was discovered.

293
00:14:34.790 --> 00:14:36.542
the Riverside Police Department

294
00:14:36.625 --> 00:14:39.169
received a letter in the mail.

295
00:14:39.253 --> 00:14:41.505
Provided details
of the three killings.

296
00:14:41.589 --> 00:14:44.884
It was unreleased information
only the police would know.

297
00:14:44.967 --> 00:14:46.886
which basically proves
whoever wrote it

298
00:14:46.969 --> 00:14:48.596
was the killer.
or at least someone

299
00:14:48.679 --> 00:14:51.390
who had direct contact
with the killer.

300
00:14:51.473 --> 00:14:52.474
And there was a message.

301
00:14:56.061 --> 00:14:58.314
[distorted male voice]
Thanks for not catching me.

302
00:14:58.397 --> 00:15:00.316
Learned a lot.

303
00:15:00.399 --> 00:15:04.028
Ten transits remain.
isn't it insane?

304
00:15:04.111 --> 00:15:06.572
I'll be back.

305
00:15:06.655 --> 00:15:09.325
Was he telling us he was
planning on killing ten more?

306
00:15:09.408 --> 00:15:10.993
Was that what he meant?

307
00:15:11.076 --> 00:15:12.453
This was the first time
we realized

308
00:15:12.536 --> 00:15:14.997
this was
an actual serial killer.

309
00:15:15.080 --> 00:15:18.250
It's worth mentioning
the jurisdictional problems

310
00:15:18.334 --> 00:15:19.835
that can arise when someone
commits a murder

311
00:15:19.919 --> 00:15:21.128
across county lines.

312
00:15:21.211 --> 00:15:23.631
It can make connecting them

313
00:15:23.714 --> 00:15:25.090
a lot more difficult.

314
00:15:25.174 --> 00:15:26.967
But this guy wanted us to know.

315
00:15:27.051 --> 00:15:28.218
He wanted us
to know what he did.

316
00:15:28.302 --> 00:15:31.013
and that he wasn't finished.

317
00:15:31.096 --> 00:15:32.932
And he signs the letter
with that symbol.

318
00:15:34.808 --> 00:15:35.809
[Kirby] Years went by.

319
00:15:35.893 --> 00:15:38.145
The cases went cold.

320
00:15:38.228 --> 00:15:40.189
Detectives at that time figured

321
00:15:40.272 --> 00:15:42.441
whoever was responsible
for the three deaths

322
00:15:42.524 --> 00:15:44.443
was either incarcerated
for another crime

323
00:15:44.526 --> 00:15:46.445
or had died.

324
00:15:46.528 --> 00:15:48.155
because they probably
wouldn't have stopped killing

325
00:15:48.238 --> 00:15:49.990
on their own.

326
00:15:50.074 --> 00:15:53.202
But as soon as I saw
that symbol on the ceiling.

327
00:15:53.285 --> 00:15:56.038
I realized that was
the killer from '95.

328
00:15:56.121 --> 00:15:57.957
He wasn't bluffing
in his letter.

329
00:15:58.040 --> 00:15:59.875
He hadn't stopped.

330
00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:03.170
He'd just taken
a 15-year break.

331
00:16:03.253 --> 00:16:04.088
Why?

332
00:16:05.673 --> 00:16:07.591
We're still trying
to figure that one out.

333
00:16:07.675 --> 00:16:09.843
One thing's for sure.

334
00:16:09.927 --> 00:16:12.012
If his first murder
spree had felt sloppy

335
00:16:12.096 --> 00:16:13.681
and unplanned.

336
00:16:13.764 --> 00:16:17.810
this new one was anything but.

337
00:16:17.893 --> 00:16:24.984
[dramatic music playing]

338
00:16:31.615 --> 00:16:33.325
[Taylor] The suspect
gained entry

339
00:16:33.409 --> 00:16:35.536
through the first
floor bathroom window.

340
00:16:35.619 --> 00:16:37.621
cut through a screen
on the side of the house.

341
00:16:37.705 --> 00:16:41.375
then attacks Ted and Tiffany
sometime after 1:15 a.m..

342
00:16:41.458 --> 00:16:44.795
after Tiffany sends
her last work email.

343
00:16:44.878 --> 00:16:46.880
There was bruising
on Ted's face.

344
00:16:46.964 --> 00:16:48.674
Struck by a blunt object.

345
00:16:48.757 --> 00:16:50.718
We think the suspect probably
roughed him up

346
00:16:50.801 --> 00:16:52.302
as a form of intimidation.

347
00:16:52.386 --> 00:16:53.929
and convinced him and Tiffany

348
00:16:54.013 --> 00:16:56.306
to go downstairs willingly.

349
00:16:56.390 --> 00:16:59.018
This little girl. Samantha...

350
00:17:00.561 --> 00:17:02.896
Yeah. it looks like she put up
more of a fight.

351
00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:04.189
Some of the furniture
in her room.

352
00:17:04.273 --> 00:17:05.733
her comforter.

353
00:17:05.816 --> 00:17:08.110
all disturbed and in disarray.

354
00:17:08.193 --> 00:17:10.362
The suspect zip-ties
their hands and feet.

355
00:17:10.446 --> 00:17:12.865
wraps duct tape
around their mouths.

356
00:17:12.948 --> 00:17:14.575
You see.
this guy had gotten smarter.

357
00:17:14.658 --> 00:17:16.910
He'd learned
from the murders in '95.

358
00:17:16.994 --> 00:17:19.246
Less sloppy. more methodical.

359
00:17:19.329 --> 00:17:21.165
I mean. the buckets?
What the fuck?

360
00:17:22.624 --> 00:17:24.752
Pardon my French.

361
00:17:24.835 --> 00:17:26.086
He ties the three of them

362
00:17:26.170 --> 00:17:29.548
to chairs
around the dining room.

363
00:17:29.631 --> 00:17:31.717
Deliberately facing each other.
do you understand?

364
00:17:31.800 --> 00:17:33.427
He places their feet

365
00:17:33.510 --> 00:17:36.472
in these five-gallon
painters buckets.

366
00:17:36.555 --> 00:17:38.474
He prepared these things
ahead of time.

367
00:17:38.557 --> 00:17:40.267
Like.
they had their names on them.

368
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:41.268
Literally.

369
00:17:41.351 --> 00:17:43.353
Like. "Ted." "Tiffany."

370
00:17:43.437 --> 00:17:45.731
"Samantha" written out.

371
00:17:45.814 --> 00:17:48.358
He draws three lines

372
00:17:48.442 --> 00:17:50.360
on each of them.
like the kind you'd find

373
00:17:50.444 --> 00:17:52.279
on a measuring cup.

374
00:17:52.362 --> 00:17:54.114
Except this wasn't
for measuring out rice.

375
00:17:55.574 --> 00:17:56.533
It was for their blood.

376
00:17:57.701 --> 00:17:58.744
By volume.

377
00:18:00.204 --> 00:18:01.080
Going.

378
00:18:02.539 --> 00:18:03.499
Going.

379
00:18:05.584 --> 00:18:07.127
Gone.

380
00:18:07.211 --> 00:18:10.297
The suspect used a box cutter

381
00:18:10.380 --> 00:18:13.509
to make a small.
six-centimeter incision

382
00:18:13.592 --> 00:18:16.095
through the skin
on each victim.

383
00:18:17.805 --> 00:18:20.224
And the result
was fatal blood loss.

384
00:18:20.307 --> 00:18:22.601
There's about a gallon
and a half of blood

385
00:18:22.684 --> 00:18:24.103
in the human body.

386
00:18:24.186 --> 00:18:26.522
It takes maybe 15 minutes
for that to drain out.

387
00:18:26.605 --> 00:18:30.067
but you can be dead
in as soon as three.

388
00:18:30.150 --> 00:18:32.277
The femoral artery
is at your groin.

389
00:18:32.361 --> 00:18:34.154
basically the top
of your thigh.

390
00:18:34.238 --> 00:18:36.240
If you're sitting upright.

391
00:18:36.323 --> 00:18:38.951
gravity just kind
of does its thing.

392
00:18:39.034 --> 00:18:42.621
The technical term
for this is exsanguination.

393
00:18:42.704 --> 00:18:44.248
[Kirby] Part of what really
earns that term.

394
00:18:44.331 --> 00:18:45.874
"ritualistic."

395
00:18:45.958 --> 00:18:49.920
in my opinion.
is anything done post-mortem.

396
00:18:50.003 --> 00:18:52.172
So. in a normal homicide.

397
00:18:52.256 --> 00:18:54.383
you stab a person.
shoot a person.

398
00:18:54.466 --> 00:18:56.176
you get the heck out of there.

399
00:18:56.260 --> 00:18:57.594
You don't stick around.
Every second you wait

400
00:18:57.678 --> 00:19:00.055
is another second
to get caught.

401
00:19:00.139 --> 00:19:02.307
From what we can put together.

402
00:19:02.391 --> 00:19:06.019
our suspect hung around
another two hours at least.

403
00:19:07.020 --> 00:19:09.273
He leaves the house.

404
00:19:09.356 --> 00:19:11.775
comes back
with a 24-foot extension ladder

405
00:19:11.859 --> 00:19:13.652
that he gets from his vehicle.

406
00:19:13.735 --> 00:19:15.070
and then he goes to work

407
00:19:15.154 --> 00:19:17.239
painting this thing
on the ceiling.

408
00:19:17.322 --> 00:19:19.116
And it's not a small room.

409
00:19:19.199 --> 00:19:21.410
and he goes
almost wall to wall.

410
00:19:21.493 --> 00:19:23.829
It's almost 20 feet.

411
00:19:23.912 --> 00:19:25.581
And he does a good job.

412
00:19:25.664 --> 00:19:26.832
He's careful.

413
00:19:26.915 --> 00:19:28.125
does a couple of layers.

414
00:19:28.208 --> 00:19:30.669
almost no drips on the floor.

415
00:19:30.752 --> 00:19:32.629
Then he positions the bodies.

416
00:19:32.713 --> 00:19:34.089
And all this

417
00:19:34.173 --> 00:19:36.425
he does without any neighbors

418
00:19:36.508 --> 00:19:40.012
hearing a sound
or seeing a thing.

419
00:19:40.095 --> 00:19:42.556
No fingerprints.
no DNA left at the scene.

420
00:19:43.807 --> 00:19:45.100
No motive.

421
00:19:45.184 --> 00:19:46.894
No relation to the victims.

422
00:19:46.977 --> 00:19:47.978
Three days later.

423
00:19:48.061 --> 00:19:49.396
another letter arrives

424
00:19:49.479 --> 00:19:50.355
in the mail.

425
00:19:53.317 --> 00:19:54.276
[distorted male voice]
Hope you blue baddies

426
00:19:54.359 --> 00:19:56.445
are having fun chasing my tail

427
00:19:56.528 --> 00:19:58.989
because the harvest
has just begun.

428
00:19:59.072 --> 00:20:01.575
and reaping's so much fun!

429
00:20:01.658 --> 00:20:04.161
A gruesome discovery
was made just this morning

430
00:20:04.244 --> 00:20:06.455
by a jogger
of a human head here.

431
00:20:06.538 --> 00:20:08.081
in Perris Hill Park.

432
00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:09.708
The jogger. Chelsea Lunsford.

433
00:20:09.791 --> 00:20:11.210
has been coming here
every weekday morning

434
00:20:11.293 --> 00:20:12.753
for two years.

435
00:20:12.836 --> 00:20:14.630
She enjoys the serenity
of the landscape.

436
00:20:14.713 --> 00:20:16.924
and was not prepared
for what she would find.

437
00:20:17.007 --> 00:20:19.343
My friend was just telling me
how I should bring a mace

438
00:20:19.426 --> 00:20:20.969
or a stun gun
or something with me

439
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:23.472
when I go running. and...

440
00:20:23.555 --> 00:20:24.640
Yeah. I guess she was right.

441
00:20:36.652 --> 00:20:38.320
[Taylor] On the night
of November 8th.

442
00:20:38.403 --> 00:20:40.405
the suspect entered the home
of the two victims.

443
00:20:40.489 --> 00:20:42.074
Tamara Latour
and her boyfriend.

444
00:20:42.157 --> 00:20:43.283
Glen Sandweiss.

445
00:20:43.367 --> 00:20:44.451
through a dog door

446
00:20:44.534 --> 00:20:46.536
in the back of the house.

447
00:20:46.620 --> 00:20:48.538
They were watching TV
in the living room.

448
00:20:48.622 --> 00:20:50.999
The volume was up.
which allowed him to sneak up

449
00:20:51.083 --> 00:20:54.336
on them undetected
until the last minute.

450
00:20:54.419 --> 00:20:57.047
According to Mr. Sandweiss.
he attacks Tamara first.

451
00:20:57.130 --> 00:21:00.384
uses a stun gun
to incapacitate her.

452
00:21:00.467 --> 00:21:02.552
We think the suspect
was not expecting Sandweiss

453
00:21:02.636 --> 00:21:03.929
to be home.

454
00:21:04.012 --> 00:21:07.349
Sandweiss says
that he seems confused.

455
00:21:07.432 --> 00:21:09.142
There's a brief struggle
before Sandweiss

456
00:21:09.226 --> 00:21:10.936
is overpowered by the suspect.

457
00:21:11.019 --> 00:21:12.854
brought to the floor.

458
00:21:12.938 --> 00:21:15.023
That's when the attack
with the propane torch begins.

459
00:21:16.233 --> 00:21:18.568
He literally burns
this guy's face off.

460
00:21:21.113 --> 00:21:22.614
Is there anything else
you can remember

461
00:21:22.698 --> 00:21:24.783
that will help us
catch who did this?

462
00:21:24.866 --> 00:21:26.285
[Glen]

463
00:21:26.368 --> 00:21:30.330
[Taylor]

464
00:21:30.414 --> 00:21:31.248
[Glen]

465
00:21:31.331 --> 00:21:32.708
[Taylor]

466
00:21:32.791 --> 00:21:33.750
[Glen sighs]

467
00:21:33.834 --> 00:21:35.377
[Glen]

468
00:21:37.170 --> 00:21:42.301
[Glen]

469
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:44.094
[Glen]

470
00:21:44.177 --> 00:21:46.596
[dramatic music playing]

471
00:21:46.680 --> 00:21:49.725
[Glen speaks indistinctly]

472
00:21:49.808 --> 00:21:52.436
What the fuck is happening?

473
00:21:52.519 --> 00:21:54.354
Oh. God.
what am I going to do?

474
00:21:57.941 --> 00:22:00.402
[clicks lighter]

475
00:22:00.485 --> 00:22:01.778
What do you want to know?

476
00:22:02.988 --> 00:22:04.364
The fuck you think I haven't?

477
00:22:07.367 --> 00:22:08.535
You really think
I was going to be able

478
00:22:08.618 --> 00:22:10.329
to be a teacher
looking like this?

479
00:22:12.539 --> 00:22:14.458
Standing up in front
of a group of fifth-graders?

480
00:22:16.084 --> 00:22:17.586
They'd be terrified.

481
00:22:17.669 --> 00:22:19.171
[whoops]

482
00:22:19.254 --> 00:22:20.922
[producer]

483
00:22:21.006 --> 00:22:22.174
Doing what?

484
00:22:23.925 --> 00:22:25.344
Telling my story?

485
00:22:26.553 --> 00:22:28.180
Huh?

486
00:22:28.263 --> 00:22:31.016
Trying to be inspirational?

487
00:22:31.099 --> 00:22:32.517
I can't work.

488
00:22:34.186 --> 00:22:36.271
Got no friends.

489
00:22:38.106 --> 00:22:40.442
Nerve damage.

490
00:22:40.525 --> 00:22:42.986
Feels like my face
is on fire all the time.

491
00:22:45.113 --> 00:22:46.365
I'm already dead. man.

492
00:22:47.949 --> 00:22:49.368
I'm just not in the ground...

493
00:22:50.911 --> 00:22:52.287
like Tamara is.

494
00:22:54.081 --> 00:22:55.165
Fuck!

495
00:22:56.875 --> 00:22:59.252
You... You got what you need.
I'm fucking done.

496
00:23:00.462 --> 00:23:01.838
Get my money and get the fuck
out of my house.

497
00:23:04.549 --> 00:23:06.802
[Kirby] Tamara's head.
the sculpture.

498
00:23:06.885 --> 00:23:08.512
the weird trinkets
on the ground.

499
00:23:08.595 --> 00:23:10.514
all of it was
carefully examined.

500
00:23:10.597 --> 00:23:13.058
And. once again.
no fingerprints.

501
00:23:13.141 --> 00:23:14.184
no DNA left behind.

502
00:23:14.267 --> 00:23:15.394
We had nothing.

503
00:23:16.561 --> 00:23:18.563
Until we got lucky.

504
00:23:18.647 --> 00:23:20.107
A woman who works
at the strip mall

505
00:23:20.190 --> 00:23:21.274
down the street from the park

506
00:23:21.358 --> 00:23:23.360
said she had seen a guy

507
00:23:23.443 --> 00:23:25.695
with a truck
unloading several garbage bags

508
00:23:25.779 --> 00:23:28.490
into a dumpster
the morning of the murder.

509
00:23:28.573 --> 00:23:31.201
White truck.
red lettering. she said.

510
00:23:31.284 --> 00:23:32.369
So. we pulled footage

511
00:23:32.452 --> 00:23:33.912
from the Credit Union's ATM

512
00:23:33.995 --> 00:23:36.039
at the strip mall and...

513
00:23:36.123 --> 00:23:38.083
It wasn't a great angle.

514
00:23:38.166 --> 00:23:39.418
but it did catch something.

515
00:23:41.211 --> 00:23:43.839
[tense music playing]

516
00:23:43.922 --> 00:23:44.881
[Taylor] The owner
of the white truck.

517
00:23:44.965 --> 00:23:45.924
Victor Shamaz.

518
00:23:46.007 --> 00:23:47.175
was a 45-year-old man

519
00:23:47.259 --> 00:23:48.218
living in Riverside

520
00:23:48.301 --> 00:23:49.219
who had a small house

521
00:23:49.302 --> 00:23:50.387
painting business.

522
00:23:50.470 --> 00:23:51.513
He had a rap sheet.

523
00:23:51.596 --> 00:23:53.223
It was relatively clean.

524
00:23:53.306 --> 00:23:55.267
Few minor narcotics citations.

525
00:23:55.350 --> 00:23:58.186
a B&E from a decade earlier.

526
00:23:58.270 --> 00:24:00.730
But he had a restraining order
taken out against him recently

527
00:24:00.814 --> 00:24:04.401
for apparently stalking
a woman he met online.

528
00:24:04.484 --> 00:24:06.445
That didn't sit well with us.

529
00:24:06.528 --> 00:24:07.737
We called him
in for questioning

530
00:24:07.821 --> 00:24:09.573
and he agreed.

531
00:24:09.656 --> 00:24:11.324
Mr. Shamaz.

532
00:24:11.408 --> 00:24:12.701
thank you for meeting
with us today.

533
00:24:12.784 --> 00:24:14.327
Yeah. It's...

534
00:24:14.411 --> 00:24:15.370
Yeah. Just. you know.
wanted to help.

535
00:24:27.799 --> 00:24:29.468
[Kirby]

536
00:24:37.350 --> 00:24:38.351
[Taylor] So. just to be clear.

537
00:24:38.435 --> 00:24:41.771
[Taylor]

538
00:24:44.357 --> 00:24:46.485
[Taylor]

539
00:24:51.198 --> 00:24:53.200
Shamaz continues to claim
he has no knowledge

540
00:24:53.283 --> 00:24:56.203
of any crimes.
that he simply didn't notice

541
00:24:56.286 --> 00:24:58.121
his work truck was stolen.

542
00:24:58.205 --> 00:24:59.581
We asked him
if he'd be willing to take

543
00:24:59.664 --> 00:25:02.709
a polygraph test.
to which he agrees.

544
00:25:02.792 --> 00:25:04.503
[examiner] Is your name
Victor Shamaz?

545
00:25:04.586 --> 00:25:06.588
-Yes.
-[Taylor] He bombs

546
00:25:06.671 --> 00:25:07.923
the polygraph test
about as badly as you can.

547
00:25:08.006 --> 00:25:09.633
Chose to be evasive.

548
00:25:09.716 --> 00:25:12.719
or lying about nearly
every question asked.

549
00:25:12.802 --> 00:25:14.429
In fact.
the only question he actually

550
00:25:14.513 --> 00:25:17.557
appears to tell the truth
on are his name and address.

551
00:25:17.641 --> 00:25:20.310
Of course. polygraph tests
aren't always accurate.

552
00:25:20.393 --> 00:25:23.188
and they're
not admissible in court.

553
00:25:23.271 --> 00:25:25.023
It's just a useful tool.

554
00:25:25.106 --> 00:25:28.235
But it was pretty obvious
Shamaz was lying.

555
00:25:28.318 --> 00:25:29.861
[camera shutter clicks]

556
00:25:29.945 --> 00:25:31.863
So. Shamaz manages
to get himself arrested

557
00:25:31.947 --> 00:25:33.448
after it's discovered
he's carrying

558
00:25:33.532 --> 00:25:35.200
a fairly large amount
of methamphetamine

559
00:25:35.283 --> 00:25:36.952
and an unregistered handgun.

560
00:25:37.035 --> 00:25:39.329
Looks like Shamaz
was trying to skip town.

561
00:25:39.412 --> 00:25:42.666
I. uh. just wanted to come
and clear the air. you know?

562
00:25:54.886 --> 00:25:56.596
I was at this Quick-N-Go...

563
00:26:15.699 --> 00:26:16.700
[Kirby] Okay. slow down.

564
00:26:16.783 --> 00:26:17.784
It became evident

565
00:26:17.867 --> 00:26:19.369
Shamaz wasn't our guy.

566
00:26:19.452 --> 00:26:20.370
I mean. he was a scumbag.

567
00:26:20.453 --> 00:26:22.497
but he wasn't our scumbag

568
00:26:22.581 --> 00:26:25.041
and he didn't really
know anything.

569
00:26:25.125 --> 00:26:27.669
Although he did give us
one new piece of information.

570
00:26:27.752 --> 00:26:31.089
[Taylor]

571
00:26:31.172 --> 00:26:32.632
No. I... Yeah. I saw him.

572
00:26:32.716 --> 00:26:34.092
I should've mentioned
that. but...

573
00:26:39.431 --> 00:26:44.394
[tense music playing]

574
00:26:44.477 --> 00:26:46.479
[Taylor] He started
wearing a mask.

575
00:26:46.563 --> 00:26:48.273
That meant only one thing.

576
00:26:48.356 --> 00:26:49.816
He'd seen us on the news

577
00:26:49.899 --> 00:26:52.235
and knew we were
actively pursuing him.

578
00:26:52.319 --> 00:26:55.488
Oh. he wanted to make that loud
and clear in his next letter.

579
00:26:58.033 --> 00:26:59.868
[distorted male voice]
So close. yet so far!

580
00:26:59.951 --> 00:27:02.954
How frustrating that must be.

581
00:27:03.038 --> 00:27:05.999
The great Shambler
arrives at the gate.

582
00:27:06.082 --> 00:27:08.710
We will all perish
in a flesh mausoleum

583
00:27:08.793 --> 00:27:12.672
but be reborn amidst
wonder and glory forever.

584
00:27:12.756 --> 00:27:15.050
[Taylor] A few months go by.
nothing new happens.

585
00:27:15.133 --> 00:27:17.260
And of course.
a part of me is thinking.

586
00:27:17.344 --> 00:27:19.220
hoping. maybe that's it.

587
00:27:19.304 --> 00:27:22.974
Maybe it's already over
and this guy's finished.

588
00:27:23.058 --> 00:27:25.810
Yeah. but another part of me.
the cynical part.

589
00:27:25.894 --> 00:27:28.313
knows it can't be true.

590
00:27:28.396 --> 00:27:29.773
He'll let us know
when he's finished.

591
00:27:31.858 --> 00:27:35.070
It's about 6:00 in the morning
and I get a call from Joe.

592
00:27:35.153 --> 00:27:37.364
They found another body.

593
00:27:37.447 --> 00:27:39.366
Earlier this morning.
a horrific discovery

594
00:27:39.449 --> 00:27:41.034
was reported to police here.

595
00:27:41.117 --> 00:27:43.328
at the North Riverside
Aquatic Center.

596
00:27:43.411 --> 00:27:44.871
This was a bad one.

597
00:27:46.748 --> 00:27:48.416
A group of skate kids broke
into the building

598
00:27:48.500 --> 00:27:50.627
to check the place out
and smoke weed.

599
00:27:50.710 --> 00:27:52.253
You know. just a couple
of dumb teenagers.

600
00:27:56.424 --> 00:27:58.259
They're not going to be doing
that again anytime soon.

601
00:27:59.511 --> 00:28:02.013
[tense music playing]

602
00:28:02.097 --> 00:28:05.141
When you first saw the body.
it looked like...

603
00:28:05.225 --> 00:28:07.727
like it was covered
in mud or slime or something.

604
00:28:07.811 --> 00:28:09.688
'cause it was so shiny.

605
00:28:12.482 --> 00:28:14.234
[Taylor] Coroner's official
cause of death?

606
00:28:15.902 --> 00:28:18.154
Fatal loss of blood
by leeches.

607
00:28:18.238 --> 00:28:20.448
[tense music playing]

608
00:28:20.532 --> 00:28:22.409
[Kirby] Victim's name
was Dennis Zao.

609
00:28:22.492 --> 00:28:24.035
a 43-year-old
Chinese immigrant

610
00:28:24.119 --> 00:28:25.328
living in Riverside.

611
00:28:25.412 --> 00:28:26.413
He was last seen leaving

612
00:28:26.496 --> 00:28:27.789
an apartment he shared

613
00:28:27.872 --> 00:28:30.125
with several other people
to catch a bus

614
00:28:30.208 --> 00:28:31.584
and was never seen again.

615
00:28:31.668 --> 00:28:33.628
Body's found four days later.

616
00:28:33.712 --> 00:28:35.630
and he had only been deceased
less than a day.

617
00:28:37.924 --> 00:28:40.844
[Taylor] Our suspect
had been breeding them. right?

618
00:28:40.927 --> 00:28:43.847
This particular type of leech
takes about three weeks

619
00:28:43.930 --> 00:28:46.307
for the eggs
to form and hatch.

620
00:28:46.391 --> 00:28:48.768
then another two weeks
to reach maturity.

621
00:28:49.936 --> 00:28:52.772
So. he'd been preparing
this thing for over a month.

622
00:28:52.856 --> 00:28:55.024
Coming here. day after day.

623
00:28:55.108 --> 00:28:57.944
checking in on his babies.
feeding them.

624
00:28:58.027 --> 00:29:00.864
keeping their water clean.
checking the pH.

625
00:29:02.282 --> 00:29:04.159
He might be a monster.

626
00:29:04.242 --> 00:29:06.578
but he does have some kind
of paternal instinct.

627
00:29:07.912 --> 00:29:09.289
Then he abducts Dennis Zao

628
00:29:09.372 --> 00:29:11.082
and brings him here.

629
00:29:11.166 --> 00:29:13.710
strips him naked.
puts him in the water.

630
00:29:13.793 --> 00:29:15.879
He creates this barrier

631
00:29:15.962 --> 00:29:18.465
around the deep end
and all along the edges

632
00:29:18.548 --> 00:29:21.593
so he can't get out
no matter how hard he tries.

633
00:29:21.676 --> 00:29:23.845
Then he begins releasing
these things in the pool.

634
00:29:25.138 --> 00:29:27.766
The species found in the pool
with Mr. Zao

635
00:29:28.683 --> 00:29:30.143
is called H. stagnalis.

636
00:29:31.144 --> 00:29:32.979
In the case of H. Stagnalis.

637
00:29:33.062 --> 00:29:35.356
it has this sucker

638
00:29:35.440 --> 00:29:36.649
on the front of its body
that it uses

639
00:29:36.733 --> 00:29:38.485
to attach to the host.

640
00:29:39.986 --> 00:29:41.863
They have three small jaws

641
00:29:41.946 --> 00:29:43.865
that create
a Y-shaped incision.

642
00:29:43.948 --> 00:29:46.451
It's how they get
the tasty paydirt.

643
00:29:46.534 --> 00:29:50.997
[dramatic music playing]

644
00:29:51.080 --> 00:29:53.041
Leeches will consume up
to ten times

645
00:29:53.124 --> 00:29:55.001
their own body weight
in blood.

646
00:29:55.084 --> 00:29:58.296
which sounds like a lot
but it's really...

647
00:29:58.379 --> 00:30:00.256
It's like two teaspoons.

648
00:30:00.340 --> 00:30:02.383
[Kirby]
This bloodletting-by-leeches

649
00:30:02.467 --> 00:30:05.804
process went on for nearly
three straight days.

650
00:30:05.887 --> 00:30:08.515
The suspect
just methodically keeps

651
00:30:08.598 --> 00:30:11.309
fishing out full leeches.
adding more empties.

652
00:30:11.392 --> 00:30:12.519
on and on...

653
00:30:12.602 --> 00:30:13.728
as Dennis Zao becomes

654
00:30:13.812 --> 00:30:17.023
more and more incapacitated.

655
00:30:17.106 --> 00:30:19.484
I've always been lousy
at math. but. basically.

656
00:30:19.567 --> 00:30:21.820
it took a shit ton of leeches
to kill Dennis Zao.

657
00:30:23.112 --> 00:30:24.489
Eventually. after he was naked

658
00:30:24.572 --> 00:30:26.115
in this filthy.
leech-filled water.

659
00:30:26.199 --> 00:30:27.867
he finally succumbed
to his injuries.

660
00:30:29.160 --> 00:30:30.620
Oh. and the reason no one
ever hears screaming

661
00:30:30.703 --> 00:30:31.830
from the building?

662
00:30:32.956 --> 00:30:35.333
Zao's tongue was cut out.

663
00:30:35.416 --> 00:30:37.252
[Kirby] A leech bite

664
00:30:37.335 --> 00:30:40.088
looks a little like
the symbol. doesn't it?

665
00:30:40.171 --> 00:30:41.923
See how it's
sort of a triangle?

666
00:30:43.466 --> 00:30:44.634
But like most clues.

667
00:30:44.717 --> 00:30:45.885
this just led
to more questions.

668
00:30:45.969 --> 00:30:48.638
What do these dots mean?

669
00:30:48.721 --> 00:30:50.515
What the hell am I looking at?

670
00:30:50.598 --> 00:30:52.141
We later figured out
that the suspect

671
00:30:52.225 --> 00:30:54.185
first got in contact
with Mr. Zao

672
00:30:54.269 --> 00:30:56.938
because of a Craigslist ad
he posted.

673
00:30:57.021 --> 00:30:58.815
They had exchanged
a few messages

674
00:30:58.898 --> 00:31:00.275
and then arranged
to meet up for sex

675
00:31:00.358 --> 00:31:02.569
at a motel down the street
from the pool.

676
00:31:02.652 --> 00:31:05.280
This finally led
to the big break in the case.

677
00:31:05.363 --> 00:31:07.740
Our technicians were able
to identify the IP address

678
00:31:07.824 --> 00:31:10.785
where the Craigslist ad
was originally posted.

679
00:31:10.869 --> 00:31:13.329
The ad and subsequent
back-and-forth messaging

680
00:31:13.413 --> 00:31:14.914
had been made
from a coffee shop

681
00:31:14.998 --> 00:31:17.584
in Mission Grove
on February 11th.

682
00:31:17.667 --> 00:31:19.460
This was a huge lead.

683
00:31:19.544 --> 00:31:21.671
We finally were able
to trace the suspect's

684
00:31:21.754 --> 00:31:24.132
whereabout
outside of a crime scene.

685
00:31:24.215 --> 00:31:26.384
I mean. I gotta admit.
I was really starting to think

686
00:31:26.467 --> 00:31:30.138
we were chasing a ghost
or a vampire or something.

687
00:31:30.221 --> 00:31:32.765
We did surveillance
on the place for about a week.

688
00:31:32.849 --> 00:31:34.142
The last thing we wanted to do

689
00:31:34.225 --> 00:31:35.810
was draw any attention
to ourselves.

690
00:31:35.894 --> 00:31:38.062
If this guy was a regular.
for example.

691
00:31:38.146 --> 00:31:40.481
and came in all the time...

692
00:31:40.565 --> 00:31:42.233
I mean. we were always
hoping and praying

693
00:31:42.317 --> 00:31:43.985
maybe he swings by
for a cup of coffee

694
00:31:44.068 --> 00:31:45.653
or place another ad.

695
00:31:45.737 --> 00:31:47.530
and just like that.
we'd have him.

696
00:31:48.698 --> 00:31:50.283
No such luck.

697
00:31:50.366 --> 00:31:53.161
There were three employees
working that day.

698
00:31:53.244 --> 00:31:55.079
None of them
could remember the suspect.

699
00:31:55.163 --> 00:31:56.623
It's a popular place.

700
00:31:56.706 --> 00:31:58.583
so he may have picked it
for that reason.

701
00:31:58.666 --> 00:32:01.753
No surveillance system.
no cameras anywhere at all.

702
00:32:01.836 --> 00:32:04.380
But the area does have
a large homeless population.

703
00:32:06.466 --> 00:32:08.593
[Kirby] Excuse me. sir.

704
00:32:08.676 --> 00:32:10.386
You mind if I talk to you
for a sec?

705
00:32:10.470 --> 00:32:12.013
That's...

706
00:32:12.096 --> 00:32:14.599
You're talking about the one
near Andulka Park?

707
00:32:14.682 --> 00:32:17.060
Yeah. Yeah. that's it.

708
00:32:17.143 --> 00:32:19.395
I'm just sitting there. right?

709
00:32:19.479 --> 00:32:21.105
And he...

710
00:32:21.189 --> 00:32:22.607
He comes up to me and...

711
00:32:23.733 --> 00:32:25.360
I knew what he wanted.

712
00:32:25.443 --> 00:32:28.154
"I want to hire you
as day labor."

713
00:32:28.237 --> 00:32:29.572
[Kirby] Did he say
what kind of labor?

714
00:32:29.656 --> 00:32:32.283
Uh... landscaping.

715
00:32:32.367 --> 00:32:34.202
Working on the house
or something.

716
00:32:34.285 --> 00:32:36.037
[Kirby] And you get in his car?

717
00:32:36.120 --> 00:32:38.414
-Yep.
-[Kirby] What kind of car?

718
00:32:38.498 --> 00:32:39.499
Like a...

719
00:32:40.708 --> 00:32:41.960
sedan or something.

720
00:32:42.043 --> 00:32:45.046
Like a. like a blue Camry.

721
00:32:45.129 --> 00:32:46.839
[Kirby] When I started
talking to this guy.

722
00:32:46.923 --> 00:32:49.175
my jaw was on the floor. man.

723
00:32:50.426 --> 00:32:53.096
I mean. if he was telling
the truth. this was huge.

724
00:32:53.179 --> 00:32:54.722
We even had
a vehicle description.

725
00:32:54.806 --> 00:32:55.974
But it gets even better.

726
00:32:56.057 --> 00:32:57.892
Mr. Johnson tells us

727
00:32:57.976 --> 00:33:00.269
he knows
where the suspect's house is.

728
00:33:00.353 --> 00:33:03.272
Apparently. the suspect
had driven him to it.

729
00:33:03.356 --> 00:33:05.900
Okay. see that [inaudible]?

730
00:33:05.984 --> 00:33:07.652
It wants you to go left.

731
00:33:07.735 --> 00:33:09.195
but you're going
to go straight.

732
00:33:09.278 --> 00:33:10.738
[Taylor] He didn't know
the street address.

733
00:33:10.822 --> 00:33:11.990
but he says
he thinks he can remember

734
00:33:12.073 --> 00:33:14.033
how to get there by memory.

735
00:33:14.117 --> 00:33:17.078
Apparently. he'd been driven
to a residence in Highgrove.

736
00:33:17.161 --> 00:33:19.080
where the suspect says
he needs to grab

737
00:33:19.163 --> 00:33:22.000
some tools before they went
to the so-called "job site."

738
00:33:25.086 --> 00:33:25.920
[Kirby] And that's
what brought us

739
00:33:26.004 --> 00:33:27.964
to 144 Artesian Avenue.

740
00:33:28.047 --> 00:33:30.049
After picking up a duffel bag.

741
00:33:30.133 --> 00:33:32.969
they get
on the 215 headed north.

742
00:33:33.052 --> 00:33:35.847
Mr. Johnson says
the guy seems normal. friendly.

743
00:33:35.930 --> 00:33:38.057
I mean. even conversational.

744
00:33:38.141 --> 00:33:40.351
And that brings us
to the bracelet.

745
00:33:40.435 --> 00:33:42.061
Johnson says he found
this bracelet

746
00:33:42.145 --> 00:33:44.272
in a trash container
a few years ago.

747
00:33:44.355 --> 00:33:47.650
Says he just likes to wear it.
thinks it's cool.

748
00:33:47.734 --> 00:33:49.694
Apparently.
the suspect asks him about it.

749
00:33:49.777 --> 00:33:51.195
starts grilling him.

750
00:33:51.279 --> 00:33:52.238
"How long
have you been a diabetic?

751
00:33:52.321 --> 00:33:54.490
Do you take insulin?" etc.

752
00:33:54.574 --> 00:33:56.576
Johnson tells him
the bracelet's not his.

753
00:33:57.827 --> 00:34:01.664
And then the suspect
gets very visibly angry.

754
00:34:01.748 --> 00:34:03.875
pulls off the highway.
tells him to get out.

755
00:34:03.958 --> 00:34:06.794
drives off. and that's that.

756
00:34:06.878 --> 00:34:08.046
Johnson never sees him again.

757
00:34:09.922 --> 00:34:12.175
He's incredibly lucky.

758
00:34:12.258 --> 00:34:14.218
I believe if that bracelet
had been real.

759
00:34:14.302 --> 00:34:15.887
if Johnson had fit
whatever criteria

760
00:34:15.970 --> 00:34:18.264
our suspect was looking for.

761
00:34:18.347 --> 00:34:20.600
he would most definitely
be dead right now.

762
00:34:20.683 --> 00:34:22.935
[Taylor] After learning
all this we go to the house.

763
00:34:23.019 --> 00:34:24.604
Just a normal house.

764
00:34:24.687 --> 00:34:26.189
We knock.

765
00:34:26.272 --> 00:34:27.899
Nobody's home.

766
00:34:27.982 --> 00:34:29.275
But we can't just kick
the door in

767
00:34:29.358 --> 00:34:31.277
without probable cause.

768
00:34:31.360 --> 00:34:32.695
I mean.
all we've got is the word

769
00:34:32.779 --> 00:34:33.905
of an unemployed drifter

770
00:34:33.988 --> 00:34:35.948
with a minor criminal record

771
00:34:36.032 --> 00:34:39.202
who we also paid
for the information he gave us.

772
00:34:39.285 --> 00:34:40.495
It's not going
to get us a warrant.

773
00:34:42.330 --> 00:34:44.665
And that's when I see it
above the door.

774
00:34:44.749 --> 00:34:47.627
staring us in the face.

775
00:34:47.710 --> 00:34:51.089
We kept most of the evidence
we had. which wasn't much.

776
00:34:51.172 --> 00:34:52.298
pretty close to the chest

777
00:34:52.381 --> 00:34:54.342
as far as the media
was concerned.

778
00:34:54.425 --> 00:34:56.219
That symbol. the image.

779
00:34:56.302 --> 00:34:58.096
was never released
to the public.

780
00:34:58.179 --> 00:34:59.680
So. nobody could know about it

781
00:34:59.764 --> 00:35:01.182
unless they were involved
in one of the crimes.

782
00:35:02.642 --> 00:35:04.102
That was enough.

783
00:35:04.185 --> 00:35:05.812
We called in the cavalry.

784
00:35:05.895 --> 00:35:12.735
[tense music playing]

785
00:35:20.034 --> 00:35:20.910
[officer] Big windows on left.

786
00:35:25.915 --> 00:35:31.587
[tense music playing]

787
00:35:31.671 --> 00:35:33.840
All clear!

788
00:35:33.923 --> 00:35:34.924
[Kirby] I don't know
what I was expecting

789
00:35:35.007 --> 00:35:36.759
to find in there.

790
00:35:36.843 --> 00:35:39.011
Torture dungeon.
haunted house.

791
00:35:39.095 --> 00:35:40.138
something from a horror movie.

792
00:35:42.056 --> 00:35:43.808
But it wasn't like that at all.

793
00:35:43.891 --> 00:35:46.144
It was... banal.

794
00:35:46.227 --> 00:35:47.812
Mundane.

795
00:35:47.895 --> 00:35:49.147
That doesn't mean
it wasn't a little weird.

796
00:35:49.230 --> 00:35:55.987
[tense music playing]

797
00:36:10.459 --> 00:36:12.837
But weird doesn't necessarily
make you guilty.

798
00:36:12.920 --> 00:36:14.380
There was no evidence
the person that lived there

799
00:36:14.463 --> 00:36:15.798
was involved in anything.

800
00:36:15.882 --> 00:36:17.842
other than the symbol
over the doorway.

801
00:36:17.925 --> 00:36:19.510
and that was
purely circumstantial.

802
00:36:21.345 --> 00:36:23.431
Look at this.

803
00:36:23.514 --> 00:36:25.349
That's just lovely. isn't it?

804
00:36:25.433 --> 00:36:26.893
The property owner
was an older woman

805
00:36:26.976 --> 00:36:28.227
who lived in San Diego

806
00:36:28.311 --> 00:36:29.395
who said she'd been renting

807
00:36:29.478 --> 00:36:31.272
the house to...

808
00:36:31.355 --> 00:36:33.065
You guessed it.
someone who called themselves

809
00:36:33.149 --> 00:36:35.026
Albert Shiny.

810
00:36:35.109 --> 00:36:37.028
Apparently. Mr. Shiny
was willing to pay

811
00:36:37.111 --> 00:36:38.362
for a year upfront in cash.

812
00:36:38.446 --> 00:36:40.615
so she didn't ask
too many questions

813
00:36:40.698 --> 00:36:43.284
and had only met him twice.

814
00:36:43.367 --> 00:36:45.661
So. we start
dusting for fingerprints

815
00:36:45.745 --> 00:36:47.371
but we can't find any.
literally.

816
00:36:47.455 --> 00:36:48.748
Not one print.

817
00:36:48.831 --> 00:36:49.957
which makes no sense
for the inside

818
00:36:50.041 --> 00:36:51.167
of someone's house.

819
00:36:51.250 --> 00:36:53.294
There should be
thousands of them.

820
00:36:53.377 --> 00:36:54.754
I mean.
was this guy wearing gloves

821
00:36:54.837 --> 00:36:57.673
every second of every day?

822
00:36:57.757 --> 00:36:59.675
[Kirby] Finally.
we found some fingerprints

823
00:36:59.759 --> 00:37:02.303
on a telescope that was
outside. on the deck.

824
00:37:02.386 --> 00:37:03.554
We immediately
got them out to the lab

825
00:37:03.638 --> 00:37:05.765
and ran through the computer.

826
00:37:05.848 --> 00:37:09.393
And boom. we got a hit.

827
00:37:09.477 --> 00:37:10.728
The print matched the partial

828
00:37:10.811 --> 00:37:12.021
that was found in '95

829
00:37:12.104 --> 00:37:13.231
on the Noah Lafone murder.

830
00:37:14.607 --> 00:37:16.025
I couldn't believe it.

831
00:37:16.108 --> 00:37:17.652
We might have our guy.

832
00:37:20.238 --> 00:37:23.783
The fingerprints belonged
to a Leslie Sykes.

833
00:37:23.866 --> 00:37:27.495
born December 20th.
1962 in Branson. Missouri.

834
00:37:29.664 --> 00:37:31.749
Homer Johnson.
the homeless gentleman.

835
00:37:31.832 --> 00:37:34.877
swore Sykes was the person
who had given him a ride.

836
00:37:34.961 --> 00:37:38.089
The woman who rented the house
also IDed him off his photo.

837
00:37:38.172 --> 00:37:40.675
Sykes had no criminal record.
no employment history.

838
00:37:40.758 --> 00:37:42.551
no current address.
no phone number

839
00:37:42.635 --> 00:37:45.096
or bank account and.
big surprise.

840
00:37:45.179 --> 00:37:48.266
the guy hadn't paid taxes
in more than two decades.

841
00:37:48.349 --> 00:37:50.476
Yeah. he really was a ghost.
but he was our ghost

842
00:37:50.559 --> 00:37:53.104
and we had to find him
before he killed again.

843
00:37:53.187 --> 00:37:55.314
Riverside police are asking
for the public's help

844
00:37:55.398 --> 00:37:57.566
in locating this man.

845
00:37:57.650 --> 00:38:00.319
Fifty-year-old Leslie Sykes
is a person of interest

846
00:38:00.403 --> 00:38:03.990
in what has been dubbed
as "the Mr. Shiny murders."

847
00:38:04.073 --> 00:38:06.367
The killer in that case
has now taken the lives

848
00:38:06.450 --> 00:38:08.744
of eight people
in both San Bernardino

849
00:38:08.828 --> 00:38:11.414
and Riverside counties.
and is still at large.

850
00:38:11.497 --> 00:38:13.624
We tried to do
a total media blitz.

851
00:38:13.708 --> 00:38:16.752
get this guy's picture in front
of as many people as possible.

852
00:38:16.836 --> 00:38:19.588
The story got carried
all over California.

853
00:38:19.672 --> 00:38:21.507
even in a few other
surrounding states.

854
00:38:21.590 --> 00:38:23.884
but no one was really
paying attention.

855
00:38:23.968 --> 00:38:25.928
But one person that did see
the coverage

856
00:38:26.012 --> 00:38:27.305
was Leslie Sykes.

857
00:38:30.016 --> 00:38:31.017
[distorted male voice]
Leslie Sykes

858
00:38:31.100 --> 00:38:32.643
has been transfigured.

859
00:38:32.727 --> 00:38:35.813
You can't stop him
or what he has become.

860
00:38:35.896 --> 00:38:37.148
Hail Azragor!

861
00:38:37.231 --> 00:38:38.733
Hail Drag Aul!

862
00:38:38.816 --> 00:38:41.068
You have no idea
what I am saying.

863
00:38:41.152 --> 00:38:44.030
Five to go
and then you'll know.

864
00:38:44.113 --> 00:38:47.158
Five to go
and then we'll know...

865
00:38:47.241 --> 00:38:48.617
what?

866
00:38:48.701 --> 00:38:50.745
It was a sick game to him.

867
00:38:50.828 --> 00:38:52.413
but it was also
absolutely serious.

868
00:38:52.496 --> 00:38:55.374
Would he really stop at five?

869
00:38:55.458 --> 00:38:57.835
The next murder happened
less than a month later.

870
00:38:57.918 --> 00:39:00.171
March 19th.

871
00:39:00.254 --> 00:39:02.840
The victim was a 16-year-old

872
00:39:02.923 --> 00:39:05.801
high school student
named Victoria Macenroe.

873
00:39:07.094 --> 00:39:08.179
Sixteen.

874
00:39:10.097 --> 00:39:13.184
She was alone at her parents'
home in Hiland.

875
00:39:13.267 --> 00:39:16.479
They had gone out to visit
friends in Rancho Cucamonga.

876
00:39:16.562 --> 00:39:18.272
Sykes jumped the gate
and entered

877
00:39:18.356 --> 00:39:21.567
through a first floor window
at or around 9:21.

878
00:39:21.650 --> 00:39:23.361
And we know this

879
00:39:23.444 --> 00:39:25.446
because it was caught
on camera.

880
00:39:25.529 --> 00:39:27.948
Okay. so this is
the Color Dreams palette

881
00:39:28.032 --> 00:39:29.575
by Adorable Damage.

882
00:39:29.658 --> 00:39:31.786
I am just obsessed
with this brand lately.

883
00:39:31.869 --> 00:39:34.080
I actually reviewed
their Shimmer Shadow palette

884
00:39:34.163 --> 00:39:35.623
in my top ten video

885
00:39:35.706 --> 00:39:38.417
and they are
just killing it. okay?

886
00:39:38.501 --> 00:39:39.710
What I'm going to do

887
00:39:39.794 --> 00:39:41.629
is I'm going to go in

888
00:39:41.712 --> 00:39:44.924
for kind of a smoky look
with this one right here.

889
00:39:45.007 --> 00:39:48.302
And then. you can just go in.
like. a circular motion.

890
00:39:48.386 --> 00:39:50.221
You don't have to do
a bunch of back-and-forth

891
00:39:50.304 --> 00:39:52.390
windshield-wiper crap.

892
00:39:52.473 --> 00:39:53.808
So. start...

893
00:39:55.351 --> 00:39:57.186
"Windshield wiper."
that sounds stupid.

894
00:39:57.269 --> 00:40:00.314
[heavy steps]

895
00:40:00.398 --> 00:40:01.941
Hey. I thought you were going
to text me on the way home!

896
00:40:02.024 --> 00:40:03.401
I'm starving!

897
00:40:06.779 --> 00:40:08.406
Mom? Mom?

898
00:40:09.865 --> 00:40:10.908
Dad?

899
00:40:16.914 --> 00:40:23.754
[Victoria screams]

900
00:40:29.343 --> 00:40:32.054
No. please! Please!
No. please! Please!

901
00:40:32.138 --> 00:40:34.890
[screaming]

902
00:40:34.974 --> 00:40:36.016
[gunshot]

903
00:40:40.312 --> 00:40:46.110
[tense music playing]

904
00:40:46.193 --> 00:40:47.820
[gunshots]

905
00:40:51.240 --> 00:40:58.289
[tense music playing]

906
00:41:33.908 --> 00:41:36.535
[ethereal whispering]

907
00:41:36.619 --> 00:41:42.500
[audio distorts]

908
00:41:45.836 --> 00:41:47.713
The video glitches
pretty bad there

909
00:41:47.796 --> 00:41:49.215
and it's hard to tell
what's going on.

910
00:41:49.298 --> 00:41:51.509
We've combed
over it frame by frame.

911
00:41:51.592 --> 00:41:54.261
but it's just too messed up
to see anything clearly.

912
00:41:55.554 --> 00:41:57.014
But obviously.
Sykes was performing

913
00:41:57.097 --> 00:41:59.683
some kind of ritual.

914
00:41:59.767 --> 00:42:02.394
Ritual murder.
strictly speaking.

915
00:42:02.478 --> 00:42:05.356
is a relatively
obscure phenomenon

916
00:42:05.439 --> 00:42:08.025
not just in the United States.
but worldwide.

917
00:42:08.108 --> 00:42:12.780
It just doesn't happen
that often in its purest form.

918
00:42:12.863 --> 00:42:14.990
To this day.
people still believe

919
00:42:15.074 --> 00:42:18.702
that the Manson Family
was a satanic cult.

920
00:42:19.954 --> 00:42:21.247
It's not true.

921
00:42:21.330 --> 00:42:22.831
Of course. that's not to say

922
00:42:22.915 --> 00:42:25.251
that ritual murder
never happens.

923
00:42:25.334 --> 00:42:28.963
There were the murder-suicides
in the Solar Temple cult.

924
00:42:29.046 --> 00:42:33.008
the Fall Rivers cult.
Order of the Black Sun.

925
00:42:33.092 --> 00:42:37.388
The Mr. Shiny murders
definitely seem ritualistic.

926
00:42:37.471 --> 00:42:40.391
but I didn't recognize
any of the iconography.

927
00:42:40.474 --> 00:42:42.935
This wasn't some goetic rite

928
00:42:43.018 --> 00:42:46.480
pulled from a grimoire.
there was nothing Abrahamic.

929
00:42:46.564 --> 00:42:48.566
As I told the police
at that time.

930
00:42:49.775 --> 00:42:50.859
whatever it was.

931
00:42:52.486 --> 00:42:55.864
this guy was a true believer

932
00:42:55.948 --> 00:42:58.701
and very. very dangerous.

933
00:43:00.494 --> 00:43:03.038
And this is
all crazy in its own right.

934
00:43:03.122 --> 00:43:06.208
but what's truly unexpected
is what happens next.

935
00:43:07.459 --> 00:43:12.881
[panting]

936
00:43:19.763 --> 00:43:24.602
[Victoria moans in pain]

937
00:43:24.685 --> 00:43:26.645
Somehow. Victoria
survives being shot

938
00:43:26.729 --> 00:43:27.646
not only in the head.

939
00:43:27.730 --> 00:43:28.981
but in the back twice

940
00:43:29.064 --> 00:43:30.608
and the shoulder.

941
00:43:30.691 --> 00:43:32.776
This is probably
because a 22-caliber weapon

942
00:43:32.860 --> 00:43:36.488
was used.
and just incredible luck.

943
00:43:38.324 --> 00:43:39.325
[woman] Victoria?

944
00:43:39.408 --> 00:43:41.744
[woman screams]
Oh. my God!

945
00:43:41.827 --> 00:43:43.829
Emergency workers
arrive in about 15 minutes

946
00:43:43.912 --> 00:43:45.664
and they're able
to stabilize Victoria

947
00:43:45.748 --> 00:43:48.792
on her way to
St. Bernardine Medical Center.

948
00:43:48.876 --> 00:43:52.546
I wish I could tell you
the story ended there.

949
00:43:52.630 --> 00:43:54.006
After going through surgery.

950
00:43:54.089 --> 00:43:55.299
she was put
in the recovery ward.

951
00:43:55.382 --> 00:43:57.092
and I had multiple officers

952
00:43:57.176 --> 00:43:58.927
assigned to guard her room.
just in case.

953
00:43:59.011 --> 00:44:01.513
And the hospital security
was put on alert.

954
00:44:01.597 --> 00:44:03.015
It should've been enough.

955
00:44:05.142 --> 00:44:09.313
[tense music playing]

956
00:44:09.396 --> 00:44:11.273
Sykes attacks
and subdues a nurse

957
00:44:11.357 --> 00:44:14.318
just getting off his shift
in the hospital parking lot.

958
00:44:14.401 --> 00:44:16.362
takes his uniform
and entry badge.

959
00:44:18.113 --> 00:44:20.407
He walks straight
through the front doors.

960
00:44:20.491 --> 00:44:21.659
right past security.

961
00:44:21.742 --> 00:44:24.119
and goes to Macenroe's floor.

962
00:44:24.203 --> 00:44:27.539
I mean. he seems to know
exactly where to go.

963
00:44:27.623 --> 00:44:29.375
He goes to the nurses' station

964
00:44:29.458 --> 00:44:31.752
and introduces himself
to the other staff.

965
00:44:31.835 --> 00:44:34.505
says he was transferred
from Pediatrics.

966
00:44:34.588 --> 00:44:35.964
They believe him.

967
00:44:36.048 --> 00:44:37.341
Says he knows
all the vernacular

968
00:44:37.424 --> 00:44:39.134
and hospital procedure.

969
00:44:39.218 --> 00:44:40.511
Sykes quite literally cares

970
00:44:40.594 --> 00:44:41.553
for three different patients

971
00:44:41.637 --> 00:44:43.847
over a four-hour period.

972
00:44:43.931 --> 00:44:46.600
He walks by police
and security several times

973
00:44:46.684 --> 00:44:48.102
and is never noticed.

974
00:44:49.770 --> 00:44:51.689
Yeah. including by Joe or me.

975
00:44:54.692 --> 00:44:55.693
[Kirby] He was right there.

976
00:44:57.277 --> 00:44:59.905
We practically
touched each other.

977
00:44:59.988 --> 00:45:01.490
If I'd just
been paying attention.

978
00:45:01.573 --> 00:45:03.701
if I'd just
looked into his eyes...

979
00:45:06.120 --> 00:45:07.830
I'll never forgive myself
for not realizing

980
00:45:07.913 --> 00:45:11.917
just how bold
he might really be.

981
00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:13.794
He waits
until there's a shift change.

982
00:45:13.877 --> 00:45:16.171
enters the room
for storing pharmaceuticals.

983
00:45:16.255 --> 00:45:19.049
and proceeds to poison an AB
negative blood transfusion bag

984
00:45:19.133 --> 00:45:21.009
with an industrial cleaner

985
00:45:21.093 --> 00:45:23.178
he finds
in a custodial closet.

986
00:45:23.262 --> 00:45:26.265
He knows that Macenroe
is the only with AB negative

987
00:45:26.348 --> 00:45:29.727
in the wing and is the only one
who will receive that bag.

988
00:45:31.228 --> 00:45:32.062
Then he leaves.

989
00:45:34.314 --> 00:45:36.191
Later that night.
a nurse comes in to rotate out

990
00:45:36.275 --> 00:45:37.735
Macenroe's backup bag

991
00:45:37.818 --> 00:45:39.445
and unknowingly replaces it

992
00:45:39.528 --> 00:45:41.530
with the poisoned one.

993
00:45:41.613 --> 00:45:43.240
Victoria was dead
within minutes.

994
00:45:43.323 --> 00:45:45.784
but Sykes was long gone
by then.

995
00:45:45.868 --> 00:45:47.202
This was a huge blow

996
00:45:47.286 --> 00:45:49.455
to everyone involved
in the case.

997
00:45:49.538 --> 00:45:51.582
The one victim that survived.

998
00:45:51.665 --> 00:45:53.834
we couldn't protect her.

999
00:45:53.917 --> 00:45:55.419
I mean. we were right there.

1000
00:45:55.502 --> 00:45:57.671
We could've had him.

1001
00:45:57.755 --> 00:45:59.047
Yeah. that was one
of the roughest nights

1002
00:45:59.131 --> 00:46:00.632
in my entire life.

1003
00:46:05.012 --> 00:46:06.513
Could we take a break?

1004
00:46:06.597 --> 00:46:07.639
[producer] Yeah.

1005
00:46:10.100 --> 00:46:13.729
[sad music playing]

1006
00:46:13.812 --> 00:46:15.022
[man] It was a rollercoaster.

1007
00:46:20.903 --> 00:46:22.279
Realizing
that she might be hurt.

1008
00:46:25.199 --> 00:46:30.579
then thinking
that she might be okay...

1009
00:46:33.749 --> 00:46:38.420
thinking
that she was okay. and...

1010
00:46:41.465 --> 00:46:43.801
Some days I feel
like she's still here.

1011
00:46:46.553 --> 00:46:53.435
[sad music playing]

1012
00:46:57.189 --> 00:46:59.274
[producer]

1013
00:47:01.068 --> 00:47:02.194
Yeah.

1014
00:47:02.277 --> 00:47:04.488
We couldn't touch it.

1015
00:47:04.571 --> 00:47:07.115
I think about
that saying a lot.

1016
00:47:07.199 --> 00:47:10.202
"you really die the last time
someone says your name."

1017
00:47:11.537 --> 00:47:14.748
Yeah. I guess
we kept all her stuff

1018
00:47:14.832 --> 00:47:17.626
because we didn't want her
to die.

1019
00:47:19.920 --> 00:47:23.048
Even though I know she's dead.

1020
00:47:25.133 --> 00:47:27.135
Victoria Macenroe was
serial killer

1021
00:47:27.219 --> 00:47:29.346
Leslie Sykes' ninth
and most recent victim

1022
00:47:29.429 --> 00:47:31.181
in the Mr. Shiny murders.

1023
00:47:31.265 --> 00:47:33.308
a killing spree that spans
three counties

1024
00:47:33.392 --> 00:47:35.227
and over 18 years.

1025
00:47:35.310 --> 00:47:37.104
Authorities continue to urge
the public

1026
00:47:37.187 --> 00:47:39.273
to keep a watchful
lookout for Sykes.

1027
00:47:39.356 --> 00:47:41.316
who remains at large
and is considered armed

1028
00:47:41.400 --> 00:47:43.235
and extremely dangerous.

1029
00:47:43.318 --> 00:47:44.862
Residents of the Hiland
neighborhood

1030
00:47:44.945 --> 00:47:46.780
where Macenroe was murdered

1031
00:47:46.864 --> 00:47:48.407
have expressed
their frustration at police

1032
00:47:48.490 --> 00:47:50.367
for their inability
to capture.

1033
00:47:50.450 --> 00:47:51.869
or even come close
to capturing.

1034
00:47:51.952 --> 00:47:53.745
the elusive killer.

1035
00:47:53.829 --> 00:47:55.372
It's unacceptable.

1036
00:47:55.455 --> 00:47:57.249
It's insane.

1037
00:47:57.332 --> 00:47:59.668
Somebody in the San Bernardino
Police Department

1038
00:47:59.751 --> 00:48:01.128
should be held accountable

1039
00:48:01.211 --> 00:48:03.005
for letting it get out of hand
like this.

1040
00:48:03.088 --> 00:48:05.215
It's messed up how they haven't
caught the guy yet.

1041
00:48:06.383 --> 00:48:08.135
This used to be
a pretty great place to live.

1042
00:48:08.218 --> 00:48:10.304
but. honestly.
I'm really scared.

1043
00:48:10.387 --> 00:48:12.472
And that girl.
she just lives. like.

1044
00:48:12.556 --> 00:48:13.974
a couple blocks from here!

1045
00:48:14.057 --> 00:48:16.685
So. I mean. who's next. right?

1046
00:48:16.768 --> 00:48:17.769
[Taylor] We were really
feeling the pressure

1047
00:48:17.853 --> 00:48:18.937
by this point.

1048
00:48:19.021 --> 00:48:20.439
Macenroe's murder seemed to be

1049
00:48:20.522 --> 00:48:22.608
the straw that broke
the camel's back

1050
00:48:22.691 --> 00:48:25.235
in terms of public outrage.

1051
00:48:25.319 --> 00:48:27.112
But I felt for all of them.

1052
00:48:27.195 --> 00:48:30.282
Every single victim
deserved justice.

1053
00:48:30.365 --> 00:48:33.160
And for everything
we'd done up until this point.

1054
00:48:33.243 --> 00:48:36.747
until you catch your guy.
you haven't done shit.

1055
00:48:36.830 --> 00:48:38.749
We'd already been offering
a cash reward

1056
00:48:38.832 --> 00:48:41.585
for any lead that led
to the arrest of Leslie Sykes.

1057
00:48:41.668 --> 00:48:45.047
but I convinced the D.A.'s
Office to substantially up it.

1058
00:48:45.130 --> 00:48:46.340
It ended up being
one of the highest

1059
00:48:46.423 --> 00:48:47.799
in San Bernardino's history.

1060
00:48:47.883 --> 00:48:50.469
$80.000 for just one person.

1061
00:48:50.552 --> 00:48:52.054
At the same time.
we were digging

1062
00:48:52.137 --> 00:48:53.639
into Sykes' past.
trying to figure out

1063
00:48:53.722 --> 00:48:56.975
everything we could.
which wasn't easy.

1064
00:48:57.059 --> 00:48:59.144
All his known relatives
were dead.

1065
00:48:59.227 --> 00:49:00.896
He had been
briefly married in '88

1066
00:49:00.979 --> 00:49:02.940
to a woman named
Suzanne Hemler.

1067
00:49:03.023 --> 00:49:05.108
but that was over by '91.

1068
00:49:05.192 --> 00:49:07.319
Tried to contact her.
but she committed suicide

1069
00:49:07.402 --> 00:49:09.446
in 2008.

1070
00:49:09.529 --> 00:49:10.989
We started reaching out
to people

1071
00:49:11.073 --> 00:49:12.407
Sykes went to high school with.

1072
00:49:12.491 --> 00:49:15.160
but nobody seems
to remember him.

1073
00:49:15.243 --> 00:49:17.621
Finally. we find
someone who will talk to us.

1074
00:49:17.704 --> 00:49:19.539
A guy named Jared Kelly.

1075
00:49:53.407 --> 00:49:54.950
[Kirby] How so?

1076
00:49:55.033 --> 00:49:57.244
[Jared] Just. like. agitated.

1077
00:49:57.327 --> 00:49:58.996
distracted.

1078
00:50:04.918 --> 00:50:06.294
[Taylor] A cave?

1079
00:50:27.315 --> 00:50:28.233
[Taylor] Like what?

1080
00:50:48.837 --> 00:50:50.047
It's. like. ingrained.

1081
00:50:59.556 --> 00:51:01.058
Which is metal as fuck.

1082
00:51:05.020 --> 00:51:06.855
[dial tone]

1083
00:51:06.938 --> 00:51:08.148
[dispatcher]

1084
00:51:08.231 --> 00:51:13.570
[male voice]

1085
00:51:13.653 --> 00:51:15.822
[dispatcher]

1086
00:51:15.906 --> 00:51:17.491
[male voice] Police.

1087
00:51:17.574 --> 00:51:18.950
- [male voice]
-[woman sobbing in background]

1088
00:51:19.034 --> 00:51:21.787
[dispatcher]

1089
00:51:21.870 --> 00:51:23.955
[Taylor] Sykes attempts
to break into the residence

1090
00:51:24.039 --> 00:51:25.499
of Miles and Kelly Harris.

1091
00:51:25.582 --> 00:51:28.168
an older couple
living in Rancho West.

1092
00:51:28.251 --> 00:51:30.420
He scaled the fence
into their backyard.

1093
00:51:30.504 --> 00:51:32.172
but is almost
immediately attacked

1094
00:51:32.255 --> 00:51:35.133
by the Harrises'
48-pound pit bull. Caesar.

1095
00:51:35.217 --> 00:51:37.219
Mr. Harris
overhears the commotion.

1096
00:51:37.302 --> 00:51:38.553
looks into his backyard

1097
00:51:38.637 --> 00:51:40.097
and sees
the struggle happening.

1098
00:51:40.180 --> 00:51:42.015
I mean. this was a big animal.

1099
00:51:42.099 --> 00:51:44.976
and it's able to physically
knock Sykes off his feet.

1100
00:51:45.060 --> 00:51:46.520
We know he was hurt pretty bad

1101
00:51:46.603 --> 00:51:47.896
because we find blood
on the ground

1102
00:51:47.979 --> 00:51:50.107
in multiple places.

1103
00:51:50.190 --> 00:51:52.109
Sadly. the dog's
only able to keep this up

1104
00:51:52.192 --> 00:51:54.945
for so long before Sykes
uses a bladed weapon

1105
00:51:55.028 --> 00:51:56.196
and stabs it repeatedly.

1106
00:51:56.279 --> 00:51:58.281
then he jumps the fence again.

1107
00:51:58.365 --> 00:51:59.950
[Kirby] This time.
I was not going to let

1108
00:52:00.033 --> 00:52:01.451
the same thing
happen to the Harrises

1109
00:52:01.535 --> 00:52:03.578
that happened
to Victoria Macenroe.

1110
00:52:03.662 --> 00:52:06.665
They were immediately
put into protective custody.

1111
00:52:06.748 --> 00:52:08.875
Not that it mattered.
because Sykes must have had

1112
00:52:08.959 --> 00:52:11.628
a backup plan for that night.

1113
00:52:11.711 --> 00:52:14.172
31-year-old Leo Deetz
was working the night shift

1114
00:52:14.256 --> 00:52:15.757
at a 24-hour doughnut shop

1115
00:52:15.841 --> 00:52:17.843
in La Sierra
when he was attacked.

1116
00:52:17.926 --> 00:52:19.094
[Leo] Yeah. I don't
like fantasy shit.

1117
00:52:19.177 --> 00:52:21.513
but this one's
actually pretty dope.

1118
00:52:21.596 --> 00:52:25.809
It's. like.
violence and sex and stuff.

1119
00:52:25.892 --> 00:52:28.854
It's based on books.
so it seems pretty legit.

1120
00:52:30.021 --> 00:52:30.981
[chuckles]

1121
00:52:31.064 --> 00:52:34.067
Yeah. Yeah. you too. man.

1122
00:52:34.151 --> 00:52:35.402
Yeah. Peace!

1123
00:52:38.155 --> 00:52:45.162
[tense music playing]

1124
00:53:01.595 --> 00:53:03.638
[Leo groans in pain]

1125
00:53:09.060 --> 00:53:16.151
[Leo screams]

1126
00:53:21.781 --> 00:53:24.075
[dramatic music playing]

1127
00:53:24.159 --> 00:53:25.702
[Taylor] Leo Deetz
is found the next morning

1128
00:53:25.785 --> 00:53:28.288
with his heart
removed from his body.

1129
00:53:28.371 --> 00:53:35.212
[tense music playing]

1130
00:53:38.590 --> 00:53:41.176
A security guard sees Sykes
exit the back of the shop

1131
00:53:41.259 --> 00:53:43.678
and tries to confront him.
but Sykes flees.

1132
00:53:44.554 --> 00:53:46.473
[guard] Honestly.
I was just doing my job.

1133
00:53:46.556 --> 00:53:48.099
I was wrapping up my rounds
for the evening

1134
00:53:48.183 --> 00:53:49.684
here in this complex.

1135
00:53:49.768 --> 00:53:50.685
I was going to take
some doughnuts home

1136
00:53:50.769 --> 00:53:51.853
to me and the girlfriend.

1137
00:53:51.937 --> 00:53:53.063
I saw a man leaving the shop

1138
00:53:53.146 --> 00:53:55.690
in a very. very weird mask.

1139
00:53:55.774 --> 00:53:57.525
[Taylor] The guard
still manages to grab

1140
00:53:57.609 --> 00:54:00.028
his license plate number
and report it to the police.

1141
00:54:00.111 --> 00:54:01.947
I'm just bummed
I didn't get the reward money.

1142
00:54:02.280 --> 00:54:04.282
In the surveillance video
from the doughnut shop.

1143
00:54:04.366 --> 00:54:06.660
you could tell Sykes
was in pain from the dog bite.

1144
00:54:06.743 --> 00:54:08.703
He's unfocused and unprepared.

1145
00:54:08.787 --> 00:54:10.372
Then he's forced
to ditch his car

1146
00:54:10.455 --> 00:54:11.915
after it's reported
by the guard.

1147
00:54:11.998 --> 00:54:13.333
which we find abandoned

1148
00:54:13.416 --> 00:54:16.336
near the 91
and 215 interchange.

1149
00:54:16.419 --> 00:54:17.879
The more desperate
Sykes became.

1150
00:54:17.963 --> 00:54:21.091
the more likely
he was to make a mistake.

1151
00:54:21.174 --> 00:54:22.300
That was the hope.

1152
00:54:23.468 --> 00:54:24.552
[Kirby] We'd
kind of hit a brick wall

1153
00:54:24.636 --> 00:54:26.137
digging into Sykes' past.

1154
00:54:26.221 --> 00:54:29.266
He just vanished
into thin air after '91.

1155
00:54:30.016 --> 00:54:31.226
That's when we realized

1156
00:54:31.309 --> 00:54:34.187
it's because he wasn't
in the country.

1157
00:54:34.271 --> 00:54:36.898
Turns out Sykes had used
his late ex-wife's credit card

1158
00:54:36.982 --> 00:54:42.279
to purchase a one-way ticket
to. of all places. Jerusalem.

1159
00:54:43.238 --> 00:54:46.032
I know. what the F. right?

1160
00:54:46.116 --> 00:54:47.826
I mean. we were just baffled.

1161
00:54:47.909 --> 00:54:50.120
And we also realized
this was beyond the scope

1162
00:54:50.203 --> 00:54:52.289
of our resources.
so we reached out

1163
00:54:52.372 --> 00:54:54.249
to the FBI
and asked for their help.

1164
00:54:54.708 --> 00:54:56.918
They. in turn. got in contact
with Interpol

1165
00:54:57.002 --> 00:54:59.212
and a whole side
investigation got underway.

1166
00:54:59.296 --> 00:55:01.506
trying to find out what Sykes
was doing over there.

1167
00:55:02.757 --> 00:55:04.301
What was found out was...

1168
00:55:05.760 --> 00:55:07.971
Let's just say
it didn't clear anything up.

1169
00:55:08.305 --> 00:55:10.682
Sykes flies
to Jerusalem in '96.

1170
00:55:10.765 --> 00:55:13.184
not long after the murder
of Noah Lafone.

1171
00:55:13.268 --> 00:55:15.562
and then. evidently.
he passes into Syria.

1172
00:55:16.229 --> 00:55:18.773
Now. the information here
is sketchy at best.

1173
00:55:18.857 --> 00:55:20.859
but apparently. Sykes
was living in northern Iraq

1174
00:55:20.942 --> 00:55:22.360
for two years.

1175
00:55:22.444 --> 00:55:24.404
but then flees
after Operation Desert Fox

1176
00:55:24.487 --> 00:55:26.364
in '98.

1177
00:55:26.448 --> 00:55:29.117
As far as we know.
Sykes didn't speak Arabic.

1178
00:55:29.200 --> 00:55:32.620
but apparently. he learned.

1179
00:55:32.704 --> 00:55:34.706
Sykes then crosses
the border into Turkey.

1180
00:55:34.789 --> 00:55:37.375
and then into Italy in 2001.

1181
00:55:37.459 --> 00:55:39.461
While there. he attends
a museum exhibit

1182
00:55:39.544 --> 00:55:42.756
on Etruscan pottery
in the city of Mantua

1183
00:55:42.839 --> 00:55:46.343
and gets into some sort
of altercation and is arrested.

1184
00:55:47.761 --> 00:55:48.887
I don't know
what Sykes is doing

1185
00:55:48.970 --> 00:55:50.597
looking at Etruscan pottery.

1186
00:55:50.680 --> 00:55:52.057
but he doesn't stay
in Italy long

1187
00:55:52.140 --> 00:55:55.018
before moving
on to Germany in 2003.

1188
00:55:55.101 --> 00:55:56.853
And that's where we learn
of someone who claims

1189
00:55:56.936 --> 00:55:59.439
to have had direct contact
with him there.

1190
00:55:59.522 --> 00:56:04.027
I met Mr. Sykes
when I was living in Xanten.

1191
00:56:04.110 --> 00:56:07.030
He contacted me
through the internet

1192
00:56:07.113 --> 00:56:10.492
about several books
that I was selling.

1193
00:56:10.575 --> 00:56:12.160
Specifically.
he was looking to buy

1194
00:56:12.243 --> 00:56:17.665
my copy of a printed work
from the late Middle Ages.

1195
00:56:17.749 --> 00:56:21.503
a manuscript known
as...

1196
00:56:21.586 --> 00:56:23.713
It's a very valuable book.

1197
00:56:23.797 --> 00:56:27.384
only half a dozen copies
or something still exist.

1198
00:56:27.467 --> 00:56:29.386
[producer]

1199
00:56:29.469 --> 00:56:31.971
It's a book of spells.
basically.

1200
00:56:32.055 --> 00:56:33.390
Witchcraft.

1201
00:56:33.473 --> 00:56:35.225
[producer]

1202
00:56:35.308 --> 00:56:36.559
Well. he wanted to buy it
off me.

1203
00:56:36.643 --> 00:56:38.353
but I wasn't selling.

1204
00:56:38.436 --> 00:56:40.397
I don't know
if he was for real or not.

1205
00:56:40.480 --> 00:56:43.024
but he offered
some wild prizes.

1206
00:56:43.108 --> 00:56:45.944
100. 150.000 euro.

1207
00:56:46.027 --> 00:56:48.405
The guy kind of creeped me out.
to be honest.

1208
00:56:50.323 --> 00:56:52.909
So. when my shop was vandalized

1209
00:56:52.992 --> 00:56:54.661
a couple days later
and the book was gone.

1210
00:56:54.744 --> 00:56:57.330
I immediately knew who did it.

1211
00:56:57.414 --> 00:56:59.666
To know that I came
that close in contact

1212
00:56:59.749 --> 00:57:01.292
with a serial killer...

1213
00:57:02.585 --> 00:57:04.629
The thing that gets me
more than anything else

1214
00:57:04.712 --> 00:57:06.756
though is what the hell
happened to that book.

1215
00:57:07.924 --> 00:57:10.760
[Kirby] We had hoped.
maybe. that Sykes

1216
00:57:10.844 --> 00:57:12.429
would be deterred
by how bungled

1217
00:57:12.512 --> 00:57:14.556
the last two attacks had been.

1218
00:57:14.639 --> 00:57:17.559
We didn't think he would stop.
but maybe just slow down

1219
00:57:17.642 --> 00:57:19.060
long enough
for us to find him.

1220
00:57:20.603 --> 00:57:23.523
If anything. it must have
reinvigorated his cause.

1221
00:57:23.606 --> 00:57:25.150
Get in the fucking car. Coby!

1222
00:57:25.233 --> 00:57:26.192
-This is not our issue.
-[man] Wait!

1223
00:57:26.276 --> 00:57:27.318
We can't just leave him!

1224
00:57:27.402 --> 00:57:28.319
Are you fucking kidding me?

1225
00:57:28.403 --> 00:57:29.404
This is not our problem!

1226
00:57:29.487 --> 00:57:30.405
I'm leaving.

1227
00:57:30.488 --> 00:57:31.614
[man] Emily! Wait!

1228
00:57:35.034 --> 00:57:41.249
[tense music playing]

1229
00:57:41.332 --> 00:57:42.667
Holy shit.

1230
00:57:45.587 --> 00:57:47.130
This is fucking crazy.

1231
00:57:59.184 --> 00:58:00.727
[Kirby] The victim
was Saroj Mallick.

1232
00:58:00.810 --> 00:58:02.437
the security guard
that saw Sykes

1233
00:58:02.520 --> 00:58:03.771
behind the doughnut shop

1234
00:58:03.855 --> 00:58:05.732
and reported his plate
to police.

1235
00:58:05.815 --> 00:58:07.567
After leaving work
on April 2nd.

1236
00:58:07.650 --> 00:58:09.152
he was supposed to meet
his girlfriend at a bar

1237
00:58:09.235 --> 00:58:10.904
at 8:30 but never shows.

1238
00:58:10.987 --> 00:58:12.989
He doesn't show up
for work the next day either.

1239
00:58:13.072 --> 00:58:14.824
and his cell phone is off.

1240
00:58:14.908 --> 00:58:16.910
Although his coworkers
are a little concerned.

1241
00:58:16.993 --> 00:58:18.912
nothing's reported to police.

1242
00:58:18.995 --> 00:58:20.955
I guess he had a habit
of just blowing out

1243
00:58:21.039 --> 00:58:22.999
to Vegas for the weekend
without telling anybody.

1244
00:58:24.250 --> 00:58:26.961
But he didn't go to Vegas.

1245
00:58:27.045 --> 00:58:28.630
[Taylor] The following day
he's found hung

1246
00:58:28.713 --> 00:58:30.965
from a public playground
swing set.

1247
00:58:31.049 --> 00:58:34.135
"Displayed" is the word.

1248
00:58:34.219 --> 00:58:36.679
It was a form of torture
the ancient Vikings

1249
00:58:36.763 --> 00:58:39.807
used to use called
"blood eagle."

1250
00:58:39.891 --> 00:58:42.268
The flesh of the back
is cut open.

1251
00:58:42.352 --> 00:58:44.354
ribs are bent back.

1252
00:58:44.437 --> 00:58:46.856
then both lungs are pulled out.

1253
00:58:46.940 --> 00:58:48.525
The mutilation resembles...

1254
00:58:49.901 --> 00:58:51.110
Yeah. you guessed it. wings.

1255
00:58:51.194 --> 00:58:52.779
Blood eagle.

1256
00:58:52.862 --> 00:58:56.032
It was clearly done
for dramatic effect.

1257
00:58:56.115 --> 00:58:58.117
When the Fire Department
is getting his body down.

1258
00:58:58.201 --> 00:58:59.536
they find a CD.

1259
00:59:01.788 --> 00:59:08.336
[digital sounds]

1260
00:59:12.090 --> 00:59:17.470
[soft music playing]

1261
00:59:17.554 --> 00:59:19.013
[digital sounds]

1262
00:59:19.097 --> 00:59:23.351
[dance music in background]

1263
00:59:23.434 --> 00:59:27.397
[man groans]

1264
00:59:27.480 --> 00:59:28.565
[man] The fuck?

1265
00:59:31.025 --> 00:59:31.901
Hello?

1266
00:59:33.653 --> 00:59:35.113
Hello?

1267
00:59:35.196 --> 00:59:36.573
Anybody. help!

1268
00:59:39.450 --> 00:59:40.368
Hello!

1269
00:59:40.451 --> 00:59:41.578
Help!

1270
00:59:44.122 --> 00:59:45.206
Hello!

1271
00:59:45.290 --> 00:59:46.416
Somebody help me!

1272
00:59:48.501 --> 00:59:50.003
Yo. yo. yo. yo! Okay. okay!

1273
00:59:50.086 --> 00:59:51.004
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

1274
00:59:51.087 --> 00:59:52.005
Sir. please no. no. no!

1275
00:59:52.088 --> 00:59:53.131
Oh! Oh. shit!

1276
00:59:53.214 --> 00:59:55.091
No! No! Fuck!

1277
00:59:55.174 --> 00:59:58.219
-No! Shit! Somebody!
-[drill whirring]

1278
00:59:58.303 --> 01:00:00.013
Stop it! Somebody!

1279
01:00:00.096 --> 01:00:01.806
Okay. I'll do anything!
I'll do anything!

1280
01:00:01.889 --> 01:00:03.850
Please stop!
Please stop! Please stop!

1281
01:00:03.933 --> 01:00:05.977
[ringing sound]

1282
01:00:06.060 --> 01:00:07.228
Okay.

1283
01:00:07.312 --> 01:00:08.438
"I have been selected

1284
01:00:08.521 --> 01:00:11.149
because of my direct actions.

1285
01:00:11.232 --> 01:00:13.818
I should not have interfered
with the Great One's plan.

1286
01:00:13.901 --> 01:00:18.781
And for my blasphemies.
I will be put into transit."

1287
01:00:20.074 --> 01:00:21.075
Hello?

1288
01:00:24.579 --> 01:00:25.622
Hello?

1289
01:00:28.750 --> 01:00:29.667
Help!

1290
01:00:29.751 --> 01:00:31.419
He wanted us to know

1291
01:00:31.502 --> 01:00:33.296
he was punishing this guy

1292
01:00:33.379 --> 01:00:34.422
for trying to stop him.

1293
01:00:34.505 --> 01:00:35.882
He was saying.

1294
01:00:35.965 --> 01:00:37.675
"Stay out of his way or else."

1295
01:00:37.759 --> 01:00:39.469
He was saying.

1296
01:00:39.552 --> 01:00:41.763
"This is your fault. not mine."

1297
01:00:43.765 --> 01:00:46.643
[producer]

1298
01:00:46.726 --> 01:00:48.019
Oh. but I do.

1299
01:00:49.270 --> 01:00:51.731
No. I'll carry his death.
and all of their deaths.

1300
01:00:51.814 --> 01:00:54.108
on my conscience until the day
I leave this planet.

1301
01:00:55.652 --> 01:00:57.111
[Taylor]
After the Mallick murder.

1302
01:00:57.195 --> 01:00:58.279
a lot less tips came in.

1303
01:00:58.363 --> 01:00:59.739
People were afraid.

1304
01:00:59.822 --> 01:01:02.659
I guess they had
every right to be.

1305
01:01:02.742 --> 01:01:04.035
We picked apart Sykes' house

1306
01:01:04.118 --> 01:01:05.161
with a fine-toothed comb

1307
01:01:05.244 --> 01:01:06.204
and found almost nothing

1308
01:01:06.287 --> 01:01:07.955
useful at all.

1309
01:01:08.039 --> 01:01:10.041
We excavated parts
of the backyard.

1310
01:01:10.124 --> 01:01:12.502
There was nothing but dirt.

1311
01:01:12.585 --> 01:01:15.505
We knew Sykes used
Presto brand toothpaste.

1312
01:01:15.588 --> 01:01:17.340
the one DVD he owned
was season two

1313
01:01:17.423 --> 01:01:18.925
of Meet the Furballs.

1314
01:01:19.008 --> 01:01:21.260
and his favorite drink
was 2% milk.

1315
01:01:21.344 --> 01:01:22.261
Yikes.

1316
01:01:22.345 --> 01:01:23.805
He ate there.

1317
01:01:23.888 --> 01:01:25.598
he slept there.
but it didn't seem

1318
01:01:25.682 --> 01:01:26.891
like he lived there.

1319
01:01:26.974 --> 01:01:28.559
It was like a front.

1320
01:01:28.643 --> 01:01:30.353
It was like a show being put
on to pretend

1321
01:01:30.436 --> 01:01:32.689
the person that lived
there was vaguely normal.

1322
01:01:34.065 --> 01:01:35.858
After a long day
of chasing some leads

1323
01:01:35.942 --> 01:01:38.695
that went nowhere.

1324
01:01:38.778 --> 01:01:40.405
I went to the backyard
of Sykes' house

1325
01:01:40.488 --> 01:01:41.698
to get some fresh air.

1326
01:01:43.032 --> 01:01:45.952
I think I was hoping I'd have
some transcendent moment

1327
01:01:46.035 --> 01:01:47.620
a lot of profilers talk about.
you know.

1328
01:01:47.704 --> 01:01:49.122
when you enter
the headspace of the killer

1329
01:01:49.205 --> 01:01:50.707
and you start
to think like them.

1330
01:01:52.125 --> 01:01:53.167
That never happened.

1331
01:01:54.419 --> 01:01:55.920
None of it
made any sense to me.

1332
01:01:57.463 --> 01:01:58.506
So. it was
like 2:00 in the morning

1333
01:01:58.589 --> 01:02:00.425
and I'm just...

1334
01:02:00.508 --> 01:02:03.720
you know. zoning out.
looking up at the stars.

1335
01:02:05.430 --> 01:02:09.308
And then
I remember that telescope

1336
01:02:09.392 --> 01:02:11.102
that we pulled
Sykes' prints from.

1337
01:02:13.271 --> 01:02:15.523
What stars was Leslie Sykes
looking at?

1338
01:02:16.816 --> 01:02:18.985
The area in the sky
that Leslie Sykes

1339
01:02:19.068 --> 01:02:20.445
had his telescope pointed at
was interesting

1340
01:02:20.528 --> 01:02:21.863
for two reasons.

1341
01:02:21.946 --> 01:02:23.698
First. he was looking
at Ophiuchus.

1342
01:02:23.781 --> 01:02:26.200
Now. most people hadn't
even heard of Ophiuchus.

1343
01:02:26.284 --> 01:02:28.578
It's one of the 13 major
constellations

1344
01:02:28.661 --> 01:02:30.329
along the ecliptic.

1345
01:02:30.413 --> 01:02:32.957
smack in between Scorpius
and Sagittarius .

1346
01:02:33.040 --> 01:02:34.208
It's also called the...

1347
01:02:34.292 --> 01:02:36.419
The so-called 13th zodiac sign.

1348
01:02:36.502 --> 01:02:38.463
although that's getting
into astrology

1349
01:02:38.546 --> 01:02:40.089
and not hard science.

1350
01:02:40.173 --> 01:02:43.134
My wife would kill me
for explaining it that way.

1351
01:02:43.217 --> 01:02:45.094
The ancient Greeks
were the one that named

1352
01:02:45.178 --> 01:02:47.096
all the constellations
as we know them today.

1353
01:02:47.180 --> 01:02:50.892
Pisces is a fish.
Taurus is a bull. etc.

1354
01:02:50.975 --> 01:02:53.686
Ophiuchus is
the serpent bearer.

1355
01:02:53.770 --> 01:02:56.856
a man battling a giant snake.

1356
01:02:56.939 --> 01:02:58.524
The reason I mention Ophiuchus

1357
01:02:58.608 --> 01:03:00.401
is because a rare
celestial event

1358
01:03:00.485 --> 01:03:02.111
was taking place
in its constellational

1359
01:03:02.195 --> 01:03:03.988
borders that exact month.

1360
01:03:04.071 --> 01:03:05.531
A planetary alignment

1361
01:03:05.615 --> 01:03:07.867
where Mercury.
Jupiter. and Saturn

1362
01:03:07.950 --> 01:03:10.244
come in earshot of each other

1363
01:03:10.328 --> 01:03:13.080
in a way that happens
once every 800 years or so.

1364
01:03:13.164 --> 01:03:15.166
This is a real thing.
you can look it up.

1365
01:03:15.249 --> 01:03:17.376
May 13th. 2011.

1366
01:03:17.460 --> 01:03:19.629
You could view it
with a naked eye.

1367
01:03:19.712 --> 01:03:22.799
But only for a few hours.
which is why it's so special.

1368
01:03:24.175 --> 01:03:26.260
The symbol.

1369
01:03:26.344 --> 01:03:27.637
A leech bite.

1370
01:03:29.806 --> 01:03:32.225
Mercury. Jupiter. Saturn.

1371
01:03:33.559 --> 01:03:36.813
The rare planetary alignment
that was only a few weeks away.

1372
01:03:38.731 --> 01:03:40.399
So. is this all
one big coincidence?

1373
01:03:41.943 --> 01:03:43.444
One thing they really drill
into your brain

1374
01:03:43.528 --> 01:03:45.321
at the Academy is
that the human mind

1375
01:03:45.404 --> 01:03:47.323
is very adept
at finding patterns

1376
01:03:47.406 --> 01:03:49.617
in things.
even if they aren't there.

1377
01:03:50.827 --> 01:03:51.911
They tell you
to watch out for it.

1378
01:03:51.994 --> 01:03:53.287
to not get carried away.

1379
01:03:53.371 --> 01:03:55.790
to remember Occam's razor.

1380
01:03:55.873 --> 01:03:58.918
The simplest explanation
is usually the correct one.

1381
01:04:01.629 --> 01:04:04.549
But sometimes.
it's actually the strangest.

1382
01:04:06.008 --> 01:04:07.885
We had brough in
these big halogen lights

1383
01:04:07.969 --> 01:04:09.387
to Sykes' house
because the place

1384
01:04:09.470 --> 01:04:11.055
was so dark at night.

1385
01:04:11.138 --> 01:04:13.975
But as soon as we turned it on.
it blew a fuse.

1386
01:04:14.058 --> 01:04:16.561
So. one of the deputies is
trying to reset the breaker

1387
01:04:16.644 --> 01:04:20.064
and realized the subpanel
in the closet wasn't working.

1388
01:04:20.147 --> 01:04:21.566
As he's messing with it.

1389
01:04:21.649 --> 01:04:23.943
the whole thing
just comes out of the wall.

1390
01:04:24.026 --> 01:04:26.904
Like everything in that house.
it was a fake .

1391
01:04:26.988 --> 01:04:29.740
Behind it. there was a space
with a lockbox.

1392
01:04:29.824 --> 01:04:31.117
Of course. we cleared the house

1393
01:04:31.200 --> 01:04:32.201
and called the bomb squad.

1394
01:04:32.285 --> 01:04:33.536
just in case.

1395
01:04:33.619 --> 01:04:34.579
They used
one of those little robots

1396
01:04:34.662 --> 01:04:35.580
and everything.

1397
01:04:35.663 --> 01:04:37.123
No bomb.

1398
01:04:37.206 --> 01:04:39.584
But that didn't seem
like his style. anyway.

1399
01:04:39.667 --> 01:04:41.043
The box was just a cheapo.

1400
01:04:41.127 --> 01:04:43.754
we just pried it open
with a crowbar.

1401
01:04:43.838 --> 01:04:46.549
And inside. just two things.

1402
01:04:46.632 --> 01:04:48.134
Leslie Sykes' passport.

1403
01:04:48.217 --> 01:04:50.094
expired from 2003.

1404
01:04:51.345 --> 01:04:53.890
and a key
with an attached keychain.

1405
01:04:59.437 --> 01:05:00.771
[Kirby] We drove over there
straight away

1406
01:05:00.855 --> 01:05:03.024
and went inside the unit.

1407
01:05:03.107 --> 01:05:04.650
In retrospect.
it was pretty stupid of us.

1408
01:05:04.734 --> 01:05:06.235
I mean. the thing
could've been booby-trapped.

1409
01:05:06.319 --> 01:05:08.362
or he could've been waiting
in there for us.

1410
01:05:08.446 --> 01:05:10.197
Who knows.

1411
01:05:10.281 --> 01:05:11.908
But it felt like we'd run
out of time.

1412
01:05:12.867 --> 01:05:14.368
We just got lucky.

1413
01:05:14.452 --> 01:05:16.704
Everywhere my light goes.
you can go. okay?

1414
01:05:16.787 --> 01:05:21.375
Jackpot. winning-lotto-ticket.
royal-flush lucky.

1415
01:05:21.459 --> 01:05:27.924
[tense music playing]

1416
01:05:35.431 --> 01:05:37.475
Here's why we never
get fingerprints.

1417
01:05:37.558 --> 01:05:40.770
Guy wears
a full-on hazmat suit.

1418
01:05:40.853 --> 01:05:45.107
This is the mold. we believe.
for the mask he's been seen in.

1419
01:05:46.484 --> 01:05:48.194
Yeah. this guy
is big into space.

1420
01:05:48.277 --> 01:05:49.570
[officer] Over here.

1421
01:05:49.654 --> 01:05:50.821
[Kirby] Real big.

1422
01:05:51.906 --> 01:05:53.574
[Taylor]

1423
01:05:53.658 --> 01:05:54.825
[Kirby chuckles]

1424
01:05:54.909 --> 01:05:56.410
Oh. you gotta check this out.

1425
01:05:56.494 --> 01:06:01.624
This is...
early-childhood reading for...

1426
01:06:01.707 --> 01:06:04.418
"Celestial Witchcraft
of Early England."

1427
01:06:04.502 --> 01:06:07.588
[tense music playing]

1428
01:06:07.672 --> 01:06:09.090
This right here

1429
01:06:09.173 --> 01:06:11.634
we think is Dennis Zao's
tongue. alright?

1430
01:06:11.717 --> 01:06:13.552
Unless he's cut out
other tongues.

1431
01:06:15.054 --> 01:06:19.016
This here's Victoria Macenroe.
we think it is because it's...

1432
01:06:19.100 --> 01:06:20.851
We watched her hair
get cut off.

1433
01:06:20.935 --> 01:06:23.020
And that is Saroj Mallick.

1434
01:06:23.104 --> 01:06:26.065
[tense music playing]

1435
01:06:26.148 --> 01:06:27.525
[Kirby]
He's been here recently.

1436
01:06:27.608 --> 01:06:28.818
[Taylor] Yeah.

1437
01:06:28.901 --> 01:06:30.236
[Kirby exhales]

1438
01:06:30.319 --> 01:06:32.655
Over here is what we think

1439
01:06:32.738 --> 01:06:33.990
is Sheridans' blood.

1440
01:06:37.243 --> 01:06:38.244
[officer]
What's this shit up here?

1441
01:06:39.745 --> 01:06:42.289
[Kirby] "Hail Azragor."

1442
01:06:44.792 --> 01:06:47.545
And then this weird...

1443
01:06:47.628 --> 01:06:48.671
altar.

1444
01:06:50.089 --> 01:06:52.091
Is this Azragor?

1445
01:06:52.174 --> 01:06:54.260
[producer]

1446
01:06:54.343 --> 01:06:56.012
[Jonas] Azragor? No.

1447
01:06:56.095 --> 01:06:58.597
[producer] How about Kaliban?

1448
01:06:58.681 --> 01:07:00.891
Like in Shakespeare?

1449
01:07:00.975 --> 01:07:03.102
The Thorn of Time
sounds familiar.

1450
01:07:03.185 --> 01:07:05.354
I've heard that.
Where have I heard that?

1451
01:07:05.438 --> 01:07:07.231
This is pre-cuneiform

1452
01:07:07.314 --> 01:07:10.651
so it's all very cryptic.
but here.

1453
01:07:10.735 --> 01:07:15.489
[reads in foreign language]

1454
01:07:17.116 --> 01:07:21.454
"The temple of the outer gate

1455
01:07:21.537 --> 01:07:25.207
beyond the thorn of time."

1456
01:07:25.291 --> 01:07:26.333
[inaudible]

1457
01:07:26.417 --> 01:07:27.460
I've heard before.

1458
01:07:27.543 --> 01:07:29.670
That means...

1459
01:07:29.754 --> 01:07:31.130
Kronung.

1460
01:07:31.213 --> 01:07:32.506
Crowning...

1461
01:07:33.924 --> 01:07:35.051
Coronation.

1462
01:07:37.762 --> 01:07:39.722
[Kirby] Whereas before
we had little to no evidence

1463
01:07:39.805 --> 01:07:43.142
to go on.
we now had way too much.

1464
01:07:43.225 --> 01:07:45.019
Sykes had collected
tons of information

1465
01:07:45.102 --> 01:07:46.479
on each of his victims.
had them all

1466
01:07:46.562 --> 01:07:47.938
in a filing cabinet.

1467
01:07:48.022 --> 01:07:49.565
Criminal history.
medical records.

1468
01:07:49.648 --> 01:07:51.484
information the public
does not have access to.

1469
01:07:51.567 --> 01:07:52.943
so he must've been paying
off cops

1470
01:07:53.027 --> 01:07:54.904
or private investigators.

1471
01:07:54.987 --> 01:07:57.364
And every murder had been
meticulously documented.

1472
01:07:57.448 --> 01:07:59.033
There were photos. drawings.

1473
01:07:59.116 --> 01:08:00.910
hundreds of hand-written pages

1474
01:08:00.993 --> 01:08:03.412
by Sykes with his ramblings.

1475
01:08:03.496 --> 01:08:06.332
A pure window
into a man's madness.

1476
01:08:06.415 --> 01:08:07.833
[Taylor]
We were pulling all-nighters

1477
01:08:07.917 --> 01:08:09.752
in that horrible space.

1478
01:08:09.835 --> 01:08:11.545
Even after
the bodies were removed.

1479
01:08:11.629 --> 01:08:13.506
the smell never went away.

1480
01:08:13.589 --> 01:08:14.673
We were going crazy.

1481
01:08:16.050 --> 01:08:17.760
On May 8th.
the manager of the place

1482
01:08:17.843 --> 01:08:19.178
comes looking for us.

1483
01:08:19.261 --> 01:08:21.847
Someone sent mail
to the office for us.

1484
01:08:21.931 --> 01:08:23.265
It was another letter.

1485
01:08:26.310 --> 01:08:27.937
[distorted male voice]
The great lord

1486
01:08:28.020 --> 01:08:30.147
of the threshold
has arrived at the gate .

1487
01:08:30.231 --> 01:08:32.358
The great rectification.

1488
01:08:32.441 --> 01:08:34.944
the final extirpation.

1489
01:08:35.027 --> 01:08:36.612
The dawn of Kaliban.

1490
01:08:37.863 --> 01:08:38.989
One left for me.

1491
01:08:39.073 --> 01:08:41.367
then he's set free.

1492
01:08:41.450 --> 01:08:42.827
[dial tone]

1493
01:08:42.910 --> 01:08:45.204
[dispatcher]

1494
01:08:45.287 --> 01:08:47.623
[woman]

1495
01:08:47.706 --> 01:08:49.125
[dispatcher]

1496
01:08:49.208 --> 01:08:51.252
[woman screams]

1497
01:08:51.335 --> 01:08:54.380
[indistinct loud noises]

1498
01:08:55.673 --> 01:08:57.258
[dial tone]

1499
01:08:57.341 --> 01:08:59.635
Around midnight on May 12th.

1500
01:08:59.718 --> 01:09:01.095
Sykes breaks into the home

1501
01:09:01.178 --> 01:09:03.055
of Glenn
and Stephanie Courtland

1502
01:09:03.139 --> 01:09:04.640
via a garage window

1503
01:09:04.723 --> 01:09:06.559
and abducts
their three-month-old baby.

1504
01:09:06.642 --> 01:09:07.768
Sawyer.

1505
01:09:09.478 --> 01:09:16.318
[tense music playing]

1506
01:09:25.035 --> 01:09:27.371
[baby crying]

1507
01:09:45.139 --> 01:09:46.515
He could've killed that child

1508
01:09:46.599 --> 01:09:48.017
in his crib
right then and there.

1509
01:09:48.100 --> 01:09:49.393
but he was waiting.

1510
01:09:49.476 --> 01:09:50.644
I mean. he was deliberately

1511
01:09:50.728 --> 01:09:52.188
waiting for something.

1512
01:09:53.480 --> 01:09:54.440
But what?

1513
01:09:54.523 --> 01:09:56.108
But we had no idea where Sykes

1514
01:09:56.192 --> 01:09:57.651
was going
or what his plan was.

1515
01:09:57.735 --> 01:09:59.195
but it didn't seem
like a coincidence

1516
01:09:59.278 --> 01:10:01.363
that the triangle in the sky

1517
01:10:01.447 --> 01:10:04.200
was supposed to appear
that morning.

1518
01:10:04.283 --> 01:10:06.452
That was a Friday. by the way.

1519
01:10:06.535 --> 01:10:07.786
The 13th.

1520
01:10:08.954 --> 01:10:10.206
Coincidence. right?

1521
01:10:12.708 --> 01:10:15.169
I am just getting to work.
it's around 3:00 a.m..

1522
01:10:16.253 --> 01:10:17.838
and... Let's see.

1523
01:10:17.922 --> 01:10:19.924
Okay. right here.

1524
01:10:20.007 --> 01:10:21.842
Right here. not 20 feet
from where I found

1525
01:10:21.926 --> 01:10:23.802
that woman's body.

1526
01:10:23.886 --> 01:10:26.263
I see this red SUV parked.

1527
01:10:26.347 --> 01:10:27.806
The vehicle is empty.

1528
01:10:27.890 --> 01:10:29.475
I just got a weird vibe.

1529
01:10:29.558 --> 01:10:31.018
So. I called it in.

1530
01:10:31.101 --> 01:10:33.229
I immediately got a reply

1531
01:10:33.312 --> 01:10:35.147
that the automobile
has been stolen.

1532
01:10:35.231 --> 01:10:39.026
and that the driver
is armed and dangerous.

1533
01:10:39.109 --> 01:10:40.444
Now. I...

1534
01:10:40.527 --> 01:10:42.738
I watched the news closely

1535
01:10:42.821 --> 01:10:44.365
and I was like.
"Is this Mr. Shiny?"

1536
01:10:44.448 --> 01:10:47.117
They found Sykes' SUV

1537
01:10:47.201 --> 01:10:48.702
right in the spot
of the very first murder

1538
01:10:48.786 --> 01:10:50.496
in '93.

1539
01:10:50.579 --> 01:10:52.790
He ran out of gas right there.

1540
01:10:52.873 --> 01:10:54.375
of all places.

1541
01:10:54.458 --> 01:10:55.417
What are the odds?

1542
01:10:57.503 --> 01:10:59.797
[Taylor]
This three-planet alignment

1543
01:10:59.880 --> 01:11:03.759
was going to be visible
between 6:00 and 6:30 a.m.

1544
01:11:03.842 --> 01:11:05.511
I mean. that gave us
just a matter of hours

1545
01:11:05.594 --> 01:11:07.680
to find Sykes and baby Sawyer.

1546
01:11:07.763 --> 01:11:10.891
But one way or another.
this thing was going to end.

1547
01:11:10.975 --> 01:11:15.062
[tense music playing]

1548
01:11:15.145 --> 01:11:18.065
[insect chirping]

1549
01:11:20.651 --> 01:11:22.569
[woman 1]
But [inaudible]. that...

1550
01:11:22.653 --> 01:11:25.155
That's a pretty
believable thing

1551
01:11:25.239 --> 01:11:26.949
that he died. I don't know.

1552
01:11:27.032 --> 01:11:28.284
-I...
-[woman 2] I don't know.

1553
01:11:28.367 --> 01:11:29.535
[woman 1]
I believe that's the case.

1554
01:11:29.618 --> 01:11:30.828
[woman 2] Do you want
a marshmallow?

1555
01:11:30.911 --> 01:11:32.121
-[woman 3] Ready.
-[woman 1] Yeah.

1556
01:11:32.204 --> 01:11:33.122
Made the s'mores.

1557
01:11:33.205 --> 01:11:34.873
-[woman screams]
-Oh!

1558
01:11:34.957 --> 01:11:36.250
I said I was going to do it.

1559
01:11:36.333 --> 01:11:37.960
-[woman laughing]
-Mm.

1560
01:11:38.043 --> 01:11:39.378
This is disgusting.
I'm so sorry.

1561
01:11:39.461 --> 01:11:40.921
[woman laughing]

1562
01:11:41.005 --> 01:11:42.756
We all went to UC Riverside
together.

1563
01:11:42.840 --> 01:11:45.551
but I was moving out of state
for my Master's degree.

1564
01:11:45.634 --> 01:11:48.345
so it was sort of a last hurrah

1565
01:11:48.429 --> 01:11:49.930
with the girls.

1566
01:11:50.014 --> 01:11:51.807
We didn't even know that thing

1567
01:11:51.890 --> 01:11:54.351
with the planets
was even happening.

1568
01:11:54.435 --> 01:11:56.312
[woman 1] I think we're
just getting old. dude.

1569
01:11:57.646 --> 01:11:59.606
Old asses for life.

1570
01:11:59.690 --> 01:12:00.733
[woman 1 laughs]

1571
01:12:00.816 --> 01:12:02.026
-[twig breaks]
-[police sirens]

1572
01:12:02.109 --> 01:12:03.193
[Elizabeth] Do you hear that?

1573
01:12:03.277 --> 01:12:10.451
[police sirens]

1574
01:12:10.534 --> 01:12:12.202
[Kirby] We had units
coming in from Arrowhead.

1575
01:12:12.286 --> 01:12:14.121
Crestline. even Big Bear.

1576
01:12:14.204 --> 01:12:15.748
but they were spread out
all over the place.

1577
01:12:15.831 --> 01:12:17.541
If Sykes was on foot.
he could only get so far.

1578
01:12:17.624 --> 01:12:20.044
but we still needed
a lot of manpower.

1579
01:12:20.127 --> 01:12:21.420
Best we could do
in that first hour

1580
01:12:21.503 --> 01:12:23.088
was two cars.

1581
01:12:23.172 --> 01:12:24.214
Two.

1582
01:12:25.507 --> 01:12:27.343
That park is
almost a million acres.

1583
01:12:30.846 --> 01:12:32.931
[man] When we were
on the way out there.

1584
01:12:33.015 --> 01:12:34.850
you know.
I was actually excited.

1585
01:12:34.933 --> 01:12:36.393
[producer] Why?

1586
01:12:36.477 --> 01:12:38.812
'Cause Sykes was
the boogeyman of Berdoo.

1587
01:12:38.896 --> 01:12:41.357
I mean.
even the FBI was after him.

1588
01:12:41.440 --> 01:12:42.775
If we were
the arresting officers...

1589
01:12:42.858 --> 01:12:44.026
[chuckles]

1590
01:12:44.109 --> 01:12:45.277
That would be huge.

1591
01:12:47.988 --> 01:12:49.365
So fucking stupid.

1592
01:12:51.784 --> 01:12:53.369
[Taylor] They started going
from campsite to campsite

1593
01:12:53.452 --> 01:12:54.370
in a grid.

1594
01:12:54.453 --> 01:12:55.662
Every tent. RV.

1595
01:12:55.746 --> 01:12:57.206
Porta-Potty out there.

1596
01:12:57.289 --> 01:12:58.582
they were shining
a light into it.

1597
01:13:01.001 --> 01:13:02.086
[officer] Who's
in there with you?

1598
01:13:02.169 --> 01:13:03.087
It's just my daughter.

1599
01:13:04.755 --> 01:13:06.006
[Pearce] Nobody's
being cooperative

1600
01:13:06.090 --> 01:13:07.591
or wanting to talk to us.

1601
01:13:07.674 --> 01:13:09.051
but. I mean. who would be?

1602
01:13:09.134 --> 01:13:09.885
[officer] Anybody else
here with you?

1603
01:13:09.968 --> 01:13:11.178
[woman] No.

1604
01:13:11.261 --> 01:13:12.471
Imagine you're asleep
in your tent

1605
01:13:12.554 --> 01:13:14.014
and a cop shines a light
in your face.

1606
01:13:14.098 --> 01:13:16.642
Like. I'd be pissed too.

1607
01:13:16.725 --> 01:13:18.227
[officer] You see anything
suspicious tonight?

1608
01:13:18.310 --> 01:13:19.395
You see a man with a baby?

1609
01:13:20.854 --> 01:13:22.106
[man] A baby?

1610
01:13:22.189 --> 01:13:23.857
[Taylor] It was a clusterfuck.

1611
01:13:23.941 --> 01:13:27.236
Heavy brush. too dark.
lots of places to hide.

1612
01:13:27.319 --> 01:13:29.655
Even now. GPS maps
in that kind of area

1613
01:13:29.738 --> 01:13:31.573
just aren't that reliable.

1614
01:13:31.657 --> 01:13:33.200
Neither are cell phones.

1615
01:13:33.283 --> 01:13:36.245
But luckily. some places
still had landlines.

1616
01:13:36.328 --> 01:13:38.288
[dial tone]

1617
01:13:38.372 --> 01:13:40.666
[dispatcher]

1618
01:13:40.749 --> 01:13:43.001
[woman crying]

1619
01:13:43.085 --> 01:13:50.300
[Silvia Vallejo]

1620
01:13:50.384 --> 01:13:51.885
There's a property out there
where you can rent

1621
01:13:51.969 --> 01:13:54.805
these individual cabins
for the night.

1622
01:13:54.888 --> 01:13:57.474
Sykes forces his way
inside one of these cabins

1623
01:13:57.558 --> 01:13:59.768
where Martin and Silvia Vallejo
are staying.

1624
01:13:59.852 --> 01:14:02.062
It's about 4:00 in the morning
at this point.

1625
01:14:02.146 --> 01:14:04.106
He's able to subdue Martin.

1626
01:14:04.189 --> 01:14:05.566
but Silvia gets away

1627
01:14:05.649 --> 01:14:08.360
and calls 911
at the cabin next door.

1628
01:14:08.444 --> 01:14:12.156
[police sirens]

1629
01:14:12.239 --> 01:14:15.576
[tense music playing]

1630
01:14:15.659 --> 01:14:16.702
[officer] Did you make
the call. ma'am?

1631
01:14:16.785 --> 01:14:17.953
[crying]
Yes. he's in there

1632
01:14:18.036 --> 01:14:18.954
with my husband!

1633
01:14:19.037 --> 01:14:19.955
[officer] Where's the cabin?

1634
01:14:20.038 --> 01:14:20.956
Third cabin on the right!

1635
01:14:21.039 --> 01:14:22.124
Please help him!

1636
01:14:22.207 --> 01:14:22.958
[officer] Stay here.

1637
01:14:23.041 --> 01:14:24.126
He has a child!

1638
01:14:24.209 --> 01:14:25.127
There's a baby with him!

1639
01:14:25.210 --> 01:14:26.253
[officer] Stay here.

1640
01:14:26.336 --> 01:14:27.754
[Taylor] The two closest units

1641
01:14:27.838 --> 01:14:29.339
arrived at the cabin
around 4:50 a.m.

1642
01:14:29.423 --> 01:14:30.549
Backup was on the way.

1643
01:14:30.632 --> 01:14:31.967
but ended up getting lost

1644
01:14:32.050 --> 01:14:33.677
and wouldn't get there
for over an hour.

1645
01:14:34.845 --> 01:14:36.263
These guys had no idea

1646
01:14:36.346 --> 01:14:38.557
what they might be
walking into.

1647
01:14:38.640 --> 01:14:40.559
[police sirens]

1648
01:14:40.642 --> 01:14:43.479
[tense music playing]

1649
01:14:53.614 --> 01:14:55.199
[officer] Check out
the front door.

1650
01:14:55.282 --> 01:14:59.495
[tense music playing]

1651
01:15:02.706 --> 01:15:03.832
[Pearce] Clear.

1652
01:15:03.916 --> 01:15:04.750
[officer] Come on.

1653
01:15:11.465 --> 01:15:12.299
[Pearce] Alright. it's clear.

1654
01:15:12.382 --> 01:15:14.218
[officer] Stand by.

1655
01:15:14.301 --> 01:15:16.428
[Kirby] The place was
deserted. alright?

1656
01:15:16.512 --> 01:15:18.138
Extremely bad vibes.

1657
01:15:19.890 --> 01:15:21.183
[Pearce] Are you seeing this?

1658
01:15:23.393 --> 01:15:24.811
I think that's...

1659
01:15:24.895 --> 01:15:26.313
that's when I started
to get scared.

1660
01:15:29.399 --> 01:15:30.526
Then we found Mr. Vallejo.

1661
01:15:32.110 --> 01:15:33.278
[officer] Looks like a bedroom.

1662
01:15:36.823 --> 01:15:37.783
We got a suspect.

1663
01:15:37.866 --> 01:15:39.117
[Pearce] We got a suspect!

1664
01:15:39.201 --> 01:15:40.744
[officer]
Let me see your hands!

1665
01:15:40.827 --> 01:15:42.079
[Pearce] Hands! Hands!

1666
01:15:44.122 --> 01:15:45.249
[officer] Give it up.

1667
01:15:45.332 --> 01:15:46.083
It looks like he's duct-taped.

1668
01:15:46.166 --> 01:15:47.292
His hands.

1669
01:15:48.585 --> 01:15:49.878
[Pearce] What the fuck?

1670
01:15:52.089 --> 01:15:53.549
-I got him. I got him.
-[officer] Get the mask.

1671
01:15:54.550 --> 01:15:55.759
[Pearce] Oh my God.

1672
01:15:55.842 --> 01:15:56.760
Get medical out here!

1673
01:15:59.096 --> 01:16:01.557
[Taylor] Sykes essentially
lobotomizes the man...

1674
01:16:03.016 --> 01:16:04.560
leaves the body
to be found like that.

1675
01:16:10.148 --> 01:16:11.441
[Pearce] It was just bad.
bro. I...

1676
01:16:13.777 --> 01:16:15.696
I don't know what else to say.

1677
01:16:15.779 --> 01:16:17.739
An empty glass is found
on the kitchen counter

1678
01:16:17.823 --> 01:16:19.658
with remnants of milk
from the fridge.

1679
01:16:19.741 --> 01:16:22.869
and Sawyer's dirty diapers'
thrown in the garbage.

1680
01:16:22.953 --> 01:16:24.830
Even then. he was still
taking care of the baby.

1681
01:16:27.040 --> 01:16:30.294
After this pit stop.
he leaves into the woods.

1682
01:16:30.377 --> 01:16:35.591
[tense music playing]

1683
01:16:35.674 --> 01:16:37.426
[officer] Closer ETA
on RO unit. over.

1684
01:16:37.509 --> 01:16:38.844
[gunshot]

1685
01:16:38.927 --> 01:16:39.845
What the hell was that?

1686
01:16:39.928 --> 01:16:41.346
[man screams]

1687
01:16:41.430 --> 01:16:44.474
[baby cries]

1688
01:16:44.558 --> 01:16:45.851
[officer 2] We should go
check it out.

1689
01:16:45.934 --> 01:16:47.269
[Pearce] Shouldn't we wait
for backup?

1690
01:16:47.352 --> 01:16:48.562
[officer 2]
But. dude. he's got a baby.

1691
01:16:48.645 --> 01:16:49.271
[Pearce]
I didn't even want to go.

1692
01:16:49.354 --> 01:16:50.397
you know?

1693
01:16:50.480 --> 01:16:51.273
But it was a baby. right?

1694
01:16:51.356 --> 01:16:53.400
Like. what would you do?

1695
01:16:53.483 --> 01:16:54.860
Imagine that's your kid.

1696
01:16:57.821 --> 01:16:59.489
But I should've said no.

1697
01:16:59.573 --> 01:17:01.199
I should've waited at the car.

1698
01:17:02.409 --> 01:17:04.036
[exhales]

1699
01:17:04.119 --> 01:17:05.746
If that makes me a coward.

1700
01:17:05.829 --> 01:17:07.331
I don't give a shit.

1701
01:17:07.414 --> 01:17:13.545
[tense music playing]

1702
01:17:34.024 --> 01:17:34.900
Oh. shit.

1703
01:17:36.735 --> 01:17:38.153
You heard that?

1704
01:17:38.236 --> 01:17:42.574
[baby cries]

1705
01:17:42.658 --> 01:17:44.493
He was doing witchcraft
out there. man.

1706
01:17:46.495 --> 01:17:48.497
You saw the video.

1707
01:17:48.580 --> 01:17:49.831
What else would you call it?

1708
01:17:53.460 --> 01:17:54.795
Yo. what the fuck is this. man?

1709
01:17:56.171 --> 01:17:57.089
[gunshot]

1710
01:17:57.172 --> 01:17:58.340
[tense music playing]

1711
01:17:58.423 --> 01:17:59.383
[officer shouts indistinctly]

1712
01:18:07.265 --> 01:18:09.393
[baby cries]

1713
01:18:16.316 --> 01:18:17.192
[Pearce gasps]

1714
01:18:20.278 --> 01:18:21.988
[Pearce screams in pain]

1715
01:18:22.072 --> 01:18:23.949
Fuck!

1716
01:18:24.032 --> 01:18:29.538
[screams]

1717
01:18:29.621 --> 01:18:30.747
Fuck!

1718
01:18:30.831 --> 01:18:31.915
[screms]

1719
01:18:34.751 --> 01:18:35.711
Fuck!

1720
01:18:39.256 --> 01:18:43.510
[groaning]

1721
01:18:55.313 --> 01:18:57.733
[baby cries]

1722
01:19:07.451 --> 01:19:09.286
[Pearce] I didn't understand
at the time

1723
01:19:09.369 --> 01:19:12.456
what exactly that wood thing
was. but...

1724
01:19:12.539 --> 01:19:15.375
You know. I found out
they have a name for it.

1725
01:19:15.459 --> 01:19:16.626
A pyre.

1726
01:19:18.587 --> 01:19:20.172
That's where the...
the crying was coming from.

1727
01:19:21.339 --> 01:19:23.633
[baby cries]

1728
01:19:24.634 --> 01:19:25.677
Sykes...

1729
01:19:27.471 --> 01:19:30.348
[distorted audio]

1730
01:19:30.432 --> 01:19:31.391
Oh. shit.

1731
01:19:31.475 --> 01:19:35.771
[loud cracks]

1732
01:19:35.854 --> 01:19:37.731
What the fuck?

1733
01:19:37.814 --> 01:19:43.653
[tense music playing]

1734
01:19:43.737 --> 01:19:47.449
I don't know what we saw
or didn't see.

1735
01:19:48.742 --> 01:19:50.368
It was strange.

1736
01:19:50.452 --> 01:19:52.412
If you looked at it
from one angle.

1737
01:19:52.496 --> 01:19:53.872
you could see it.

1738
01:19:53.955 --> 01:19:56.041
From another.
it wasn't as clear.

1739
01:19:56.124 --> 01:19:58.084
The videos don't do it
justice at all.

1740
01:19:58.168 --> 01:20:00.420
I'm just still
not convinced any of that...

1741
01:20:00.504 --> 01:20:01.421
what do you call it?

1742
01:20:01.505 --> 01:20:02.464
Karmic phenomena?

1743
01:20:02.547 --> 01:20:03.673
[producer]

1744
01:20:03.757 --> 01:20:05.342
Cosmic phenomena.

1745
01:20:05.425 --> 01:20:06.843
I mean. sky looked weird
that morning.

1746
01:20:06.927 --> 01:20:08.178
no doubt about that.

1747
01:20:08.261 --> 01:20:09.346
but there's plenty
of weird stuff

1748
01:20:09.429 --> 01:20:11.223
that happens in the sky.

1749
01:20:11.306 --> 01:20:13.934
Aurora borealis?

1750
01:20:14.017 --> 01:20:16.561
[producer]

1751
01:20:16.645 --> 01:20:18.188
Okay. but you can't tell me

1752
01:20:18.271 --> 01:20:21.024
that's not some weird looking
space stuff too. right?

1753
01:20:21.107 --> 01:20:23.318
[Pearce]
I don't remember much.

1754
01:20:23.401 --> 01:20:24.611
It gets hazy.

1755
01:20:24.694 --> 01:20:26.238
So. that...
that thing in the sky?

1756
01:20:28.406 --> 01:20:29.825
It looked like red eyes.

1757
01:20:31.368 --> 01:20:33.203
[woman 1] Jeez. dude.

1758
01:20:33.286 --> 01:20:34.913
Holy shit.

1759
01:20:34.996 --> 01:20:36.832
What the fuck?

1760
01:20:41.002 --> 01:20:42.921
[woman 1]
What the fuck is that?

1761
01:20:43.004 --> 01:20:44.256
[Elizabeth] I don't know. dude.

1762
01:20:46.091 --> 01:20:48.176
[woman 1] Lizzie?

1763
01:20:48.260 --> 01:20:49.177
Lizzie?

1764
01:20:50.929 --> 01:20:51.847
Lizzie!

1765
01:20:53.765 --> 01:20:55.225
Liz!

1766
01:20:55.308 --> 01:20:56.434
Dude. Lizzie!

1767
01:20:56.518 --> 01:20:58.478
Lizzie! Lizzie! Lizzie!

1768
01:20:59.771 --> 01:21:01.982
Lizzie! Kate! Kate. wake up!

1769
01:21:02.065 --> 01:21:04.401
I need you to call 911!
Kate. please!

1770
01:21:04.484 --> 01:21:10.866
[tense music playing]

1771
01:21:16.788 --> 01:21:21.960
[Pearce shouts indistinctly]

1772
01:21:22.043 --> 01:21:23.295
[gunshot]

1773
01:21:23.378 --> 01:21:25.171
[police sirens]

1774
01:21:25.255 --> 01:21:27.340
[baby crying]

1775
01:21:27.424 --> 01:21:30.760
[Pearce groans]

1776
01:21:30.844 --> 01:21:33.179
[Kirby] And just like that.
it was over.

1777
01:21:37.475 --> 01:21:38.560
We got him.

1778
01:21:40.979 --> 01:21:41.897
[baby crying]

1779
01:21:41.980 --> 01:21:44.107
Don't turn away. just...

1780
01:21:44.190 --> 01:21:45.775
I'll be right...
How's the baby?

1781
01:21:45.859 --> 01:21:47.569
He's okay.

1782
01:21:47.652 --> 01:21:49.070
[Kirby] That was
too goddamn close.

1783
01:21:49.154 --> 01:21:50.614
[Pearce hyperventilates]

1784
01:21:50.697 --> 01:21:52.616
-[Taylor] He's gone!
-[Kirby] What?

1785
01:21:52.699 --> 01:21:54.159
[Taylor] We need
some help over here!

1786
01:21:54.242 --> 01:21:55.744
[Kirby] You've got to be
fucking kidding me!

1787
01:21:55.827 --> 01:22:00.290
[tense music playing]

1788
01:22:00.373 --> 01:22:02.167
Leslie Sykes' body was found

1789
01:22:02.250 --> 01:22:04.252
about 100 yards
from the cabin. in a creek...

1790
01:22:07.130 --> 01:22:08.882
covered in leeches.

1791
01:22:08.965 --> 01:22:11.676
He'd only been in the water
for a matter of minutes.

1792
01:22:11.760 --> 01:22:13.762
It's like they were
drawn to him.

1793
01:22:13.845 --> 01:22:16.556
They made any kind of visual
identification impossible.

1794
01:22:16.640 --> 01:22:19.392
but we still confirmed it
with fingerprint and DNA.

1795
01:22:22.062 --> 01:22:23.855
It looks like Sykes
had been living out there

1796
01:22:23.939 --> 01:22:25.815
for at least a couple weeks.

1797
01:22:25.899 --> 01:22:27.651
Sleeping
in a makeshift shelter.

1798
01:22:27.734 --> 01:22:29.945
stealing food
from other people's campsites.

1799
01:22:31.321 --> 01:22:34.616
His final time on this earth
was spent hungry.

1800
01:22:34.699 --> 01:22:37.535
cold. and alone.

1801
01:22:37.619 --> 01:22:40.789
[Taylor] No phantoms.
no ghosts.

1802
01:22:40.872 --> 01:22:42.082
A flesh-and-blood human.

1803
01:22:43.416 --> 01:22:45.460
Piece of shit human.

1804
01:22:45.543 --> 01:22:46.711
but human nonetheless.

1805
01:22:49.547 --> 01:22:55.845
[dramatic music playing]

1806
01:23:05.438 --> 01:23:06.898
So. I was...

1807
01:23:06.982 --> 01:23:08.608
I was getting up
for work that morning

1808
01:23:08.692 --> 01:23:10.443
and I was checking my Facebook.

1809
01:23:10.527 --> 01:23:12.320
and I had. like.

1810
01:23:12.404 --> 01:23:14.406
all of these messages.
and I was like. what?

1811
01:23:14.489 --> 01:23:16.324
You know. what's going on here?

1812
01:23:16.408 --> 01:23:17.993
And then I realized
they got him.

1813
01:23:21.496 --> 01:23:23.707
Like. they really
fucking got him.

1814
01:23:23.790 --> 01:23:27.335
[police sirens]

1815
01:23:27.419 --> 01:23:29.838
[reporter] The Inland Empire
can breathe a sigh of relief

1816
01:23:29.921 --> 01:23:31.464
with the news just coming in

1817
01:23:31.548 --> 01:23:33.258
that the hunt
for serial killer

1818
01:23:33.341 --> 01:23:36.428
Leslie Sykes.
a.k.a. Mr. Shiny.

1819
01:23:36.511 --> 01:23:38.972
has finally come to an end.

1820
01:23:39.055 --> 01:23:40.473
Police shot and killed Sykes

1821
01:23:40.557 --> 01:23:41.891
this morning in a standoff

1822
01:23:41.975 --> 01:23:43.518
in the San Bernardino
mountains.

1823
01:23:43.601 --> 01:23:45.103
but not before ending the life

1824
01:23:45.186 --> 01:23:47.397
of one Riverside Police
Department deputy.

1825
01:23:50.400 --> 01:23:51.401
[Pearce] Richie...

1826
01:23:54.821 --> 01:23:56.031
I don't want to talk about it.

1827
01:23:59.868 --> 01:24:01.036
Should've been me.

1828
01:24:03.038 --> 01:24:05.457
I'm here to formally
announce that Leslie Sykes.

1829
01:24:06.708 --> 01:24:09.377
otherwise known as Mr. Shiny.

1830
01:24:09.461 --> 01:24:11.463
died this morning
at approximately 6:00 a.m.

1831
01:24:11.546 --> 01:24:13.256
Pacific standard time

1832
01:24:13.339 --> 01:24:14.883
as a result of an extended
gun battle

1833
01:24:14.966 --> 01:24:16.509
with local authorities.

1834
01:24:18.219 --> 01:24:19.345
[Monica]
I couldn't believe it.

1835
01:24:20.805 --> 01:24:22.474
Like. all of this...

1836
01:24:22.557 --> 01:24:24.684
This. like. weight was

1837
01:24:24.768 --> 01:24:27.145
just lifted from my chest.
you know?

1838
01:24:30.398 --> 01:24:32.901
Like Shifra could finally
rest in peace. you know.

1839
01:24:32.984 --> 01:24:35.695
'cause that fucking asshole
was dead.

1840
01:24:35.779 --> 01:24:37.989
I mean. nothing's ever going
to bring my girl back. but...

1841
01:24:39.783 --> 01:24:42.035
at least we can all.
like. start to heal now.

1842
01:24:43.953 --> 01:24:45.872
I feel no joy
in Leslie Sykes' death.

1843
01:24:45.955 --> 01:24:47.457
I really don't.

1844
01:24:47.540 --> 01:24:49.709
I did in the beginning but.
as time has gone on...

1845
01:24:52.003 --> 01:24:53.922
I wish I could've
interviewed him.

1846
01:24:54.005 --> 01:24:56.716
I wish we could've gotten
more information.

1847
01:24:56.800 --> 01:24:59.302
In the timespan that Sykes
was actively killing.

1848
01:24:59.385 --> 01:25:01.846
that we know about. there were
over 100 unsolved homicides

1849
01:25:01.930 --> 01:25:03.264
in the two counties.

1850
01:25:03.348 --> 01:25:04.808
Could some of these be Sykes?

1851
01:25:04.891 --> 01:25:06.392
We'll never know.

1852
01:25:06.476 --> 01:25:08.228
Is it possible
Sykes had an accomplice.

1853
01:25:08.311 --> 01:25:10.814
someone that helped him.
funded him?

1854
01:25:10.897 --> 01:25:12.107
We'll never know.

1855
01:25:14.317 --> 01:25:17.278
[Pearce] He got off too easy.
if you ask me.

1856
01:25:17.362 --> 01:25:18.905
Should've drawn and quartered
that motherfucker.

1857
01:25:20.698 --> 01:25:22.367
Sorry. is...
Was that too much or...?

1858
01:25:22.450 --> 01:25:24.285
[producer] No.
that's actually perfect.

1859
01:25:27.956 --> 01:25:29.332
Happy I could set
the record straight.

1860
01:25:33.837 --> 01:25:36.131
When we first found out
that they killed him...

1861
01:25:38.091 --> 01:25:40.426
I guess it was bittersweet.

1862
01:25:44.889 --> 01:25:47.725
I was just glad
he couldn't hurt anybody else.

1863
01:25:47.809 --> 01:25:49.769
[April] We tried to keep
Victoria's memory alive.

1864
01:25:49.853 --> 01:25:52.147
but it gets harder
as time goes on.

1865
01:25:54.816 --> 01:25:56.151
Friends lose interest.

1866
01:25:59.279 --> 01:26:01.239
I think about that saying a lot

1867
01:26:01.322 --> 01:26:03.158
that goes

1868
01:26:03.241 --> 01:26:06.286
"you really die the last time
someone says your name."

1869
01:26:06.369 --> 01:26:07.537
[Jim] Honey.
you already said this.

1870
01:26:07.620 --> 01:26:09.205
I know.

1871
01:26:09.289 --> 01:26:11.541
It's just so true.

1872
01:26:11.624 --> 01:26:14.460
Ted Bundy. Gacy.

1873
01:26:14.544 --> 01:26:16.171
These guys will live forever.

1874
01:26:17.380 --> 01:26:20.175
And now so will Mr. Shiny.

1875
01:26:21.593 --> 01:26:23.344
Eight victims
were honored today

1876
01:26:23.428 --> 01:26:26.639
at a memorial held
at Pioneer Memorial Cemetery.

1877
01:26:26.723 --> 01:26:28.516
including those
from the original crimes

1878
01:26:28.600 --> 01:26:30.435
in 1995.

1879
01:26:30.518 --> 01:26:32.437
Almost 1.000 people
joined the service

1880
01:26:32.520 --> 01:26:33.897
to pay their respects
to those lives

1881
01:26:33.980 --> 01:26:35.690
taken too soon

1882
01:26:35.773 --> 01:26:37.859
by serial killer Leslie Sykes.

1883
01:26:39.110 --> 01:26:41.112
[woman 1] Lizzie! Lizzie!

1884
01:26:41.196 --> 01:26:43.531
Kate! Kate. wake up!
I need you to call 911!

1885
01:26:43.615 --> 01:26:45.825
[producer]

1886
01:26:45.909 --> 01:26:47.911
[Elizabeth] Yep.

1887
01:26:47.994 --> 01:26:50.371
Great place to have
your first one. right?

1888
01:26:50.455 --> 01:26:52.790
[producer]

1889
01:26:52.874 --> 01:26:55.668
Started for the first time
that night.

1890
01:26:55.752 --> 01:26:58.922
And I wasn't the only one
who had bad luck. either.

1891
01:26:59.005 --> 01:27:02.717
Gail randomly started
having vertigo

1892
01:27:02.800 --> 01:27:04.177
after that trip.

1893
01:27:09.557 --> 01:27:12.352
So. you know.
you asked me if I believe

1894
01:27:12.435 --> 01:27:15.897
